Attack Order.Name: Attack Order
Attack Order.Effects: Attack Order is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Bug Bite.Name: Bug Bite
Bug Bite.Effects: If the target has a stored Digestion/Food Buff or has traded in a Digestion/Food Buff this Scene, the user may gain the effects of the Digestion/Food Buff. This does no count towards the Usual limit on the user's Digestion/Food Buffs.

Bug Buzz.Name: Bug Buzz
Bug Buzz.Range: Cone 2 or Close Blast 2; Sonic, Smite
Bug Buzz.Effects: Bug Buzz lowers the Special Defense of all legal targets by -1 CS on 19+.

Defend Order.Name: Defend Order
Defend Order.Effects: Raise the user's Defense and Special Defense by +1 CS each.

Fell Stinger.Name: Fell Stinger
Fell Stinger.Effects: If the user successfully knocks out the target with Fell Stinger, raise the user's Attack by +2 CS.

First Impression.Name: First Impression
First Impression.Effects: First Impression can only be used during the round the user joins an encounter. Switching out resets the requirement of joining an encounter.

Fury Cutter.Name: Fury Cutter
Fury Cutter.Effects: If Fury Cutter is used successfully and consecutively on the same target, the Damage Base is increased by +4; the first hit has a DB of 4; the second hit a DB of 8, the third hit a DB of 12, and the fourth and all further hits have a DB of 16. If Fury Cutter misses or fails to damage its target, its Damage Base resets.

Heal Order.Name: Heal Order
Heal Order.Effects: The user regains HP equal to half of its full HP.

Infestation.Name: Infestation
Infestation.Effects: The target is put in a Vortex.

Leech Life.Name: Leech Life
Leech Life.Effects: After the target takes damage, the user gains HP equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Lunge.Name: Lunge
Lunge.Effects: Lunge may be used as a Free Action at the end of a Sprint Maneuver taken as a Standard Action, as long as the user Shifted at least 3 meters in a straight line towards the target. When used this way, Lunge's target receives a -5 penalty to damage rolls for 1 round.

Pollen Puff.Name: Pollen Puff
Pollen Puff.Effects: Once per Scene, Pollen Puff may instead be used on an ally; when used this way, the target recovers 1/2 of their maximum Hit Points and the Move has the Healing keyword.

Powder.Name: Powder
Powder.Effects: The target is dusted with a Coat of flammable powder. If the affected target uses a damaging Fire-Type attack, the attack is negated and instead creates a Blast 3 centered on itself as the powder explodes, and the Coat is removed. All legal targets within the Blast take damage equal to what the user of the Fire-Type attack would roll for the damage of their attack. This damage is Typeless or Fire-Type, whichever would be more effective.

Quiver Dance.Name: Quiver Dance
Quiver Dance.Effects: Raise the user's Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed by +1 CS each.

Rage Powder.Name: Rage Powder
Rage Powder.Effects: All legal targets hit by Rage Powder are Enraged. While enraged, they must shift to target the user when using a Move or Attack if the user is within reach. If the user is Fainted or Switched out, all legal targets hit by Rage Powder are no longer Enraged.

Signal Beam.Name: Signal Beam
Signal Beam.Effects: Signal Beam Confuses the target on 19+.

Silver Wind.Name: Silver Wind
Silver Wind.Effects: Silver Wind raises each of the user's stats by +1 CS on 19+.

Spider Web.Name: Spider Web
Spider Web.Effects: Spider Web cannot miss. The target is Stuck and Trapped. If the target is freed of the Stuck condition, it is freed of Trapped as well. *Grants Threaded

Steamroller.Name: Steamroller
Steamroller.Effects: Steamroller Flinches the target on 15+. If the target is Small, Steamroller deals an additional +5 Damage.

Sticky Web.Name: Sticky Web
Sticky Web.Effects: Set 8 square meters of Sticky Web hazards within your range such that all 8 meters are adjacent with at least one other space of Sticky Web. Sticky Web causes Terrain to become Slow Terrain, and a grounded foe that runs into the hazard has its Speed lowered by -1 CS and becomes Slowed until the end of their next turn. Flying-type Pokemon and Pokemon and Trainers with Levitate are not affected by Sticky Web. Bug-type Pokemon may move over Sticky Web harmlessly, destroying theHazards as they do so. *Grants Threaded

String Shot.Name: String Shot
String Shot.Effects: Lower the Speed of all legal targets by -1 CS. If this lowers their Speed CS to -6, or if their Speed CS was already at -6, they are instead Stuck. *Grants Threaded

Struggle Bug.Name: Struggle Bug
Struggle Bug.Effects: Lower the Special Attack of all legal targets by -1 CS.

Tail Glow.Name: Tail Glow
Tail Glow.Effects: Raise the user’s Special Attack by +3 CS. *Grants Glow

U-Turn.Name: U-Turn
U-Turn.Effects: The user deals damage and then is immediately recalled to its Poké Ball in the same turn. A New Pokémon may immediately be sent out. Using U-Turn lets a Trapped user be recalled.

Assurance.Name: Assurance
Assurance.Effects: If Assurance’s target has already been damaged by a Move on the same round Assurance is being used, Assurance has a Damage Base of 12 (3d12+10 / 30) instead. This effect may trigger only once per Scene per Target.

Beat Up.Name: Beat Up
Beat Up.Effects: The user and up to two allies adjacent to the target may each make a Struggle Attack against the target. These Struggle Attacks hit for Dark-Type Damage instead of their usual Type. Beat Up may trigger Pack Hunt only once, no matter the number of attacks.

Crunch.Name: Crunch
Crunch.Effects: Crunch lowers the target’s Defense by -1 CS on 17+.

Dark Pulse.Name: Dark Pulse
Dark Pulse.Effects: Dark Pulse Flinches the target on 17+.

Dark Void.Name: Dark Void
Dark Void.Effects: The target falls Asleep. Once per Scene, Dark Void may be used as if its range were “Burst 5, Friendly” instead.

Darkest Lariat.Name: Darkest Lariat
Darkest Lariat.Effects: This Move ignores the target’s positive Defense Combat Stages and all Damage Reduction.

Embargo.Name: Embargo
Embargo.Effects: The target cannot use or benefit from held items for the remainder of the encounter. Embargo may only affect one target at a time; if Embargo is used on a new target, the previous target is freed from the effect.

Fake Tears.Name: Fake Tears
Fake Tears.Effects: Lower the target's Special Defense by -2 CS.

Flatter.Name: Flatter
Flatter.Effects: Raise the target's Special Attack by +1 CS. Flatter Confuses the target.

Fling.Name: Fling
Fling.Effects: The user throws a held item, determining the effect of Fling.

Foul Play.Name: Foul Play
Foul Play.Effects: The target reveals its Attack stat. When calculating damage, add the target's Attack stat instead of the user's Attack stat.

Hone Claws.Name: Hone Claws
Hone Claws.Effects: Raise the user's Attack by +1 CS and Accuracy by +1.

Knock Off.Name: Knock Off
Knock Off.Effects: Choose one of the target's Held Items or Accessory Slot Items. It is knocked to the ground.

Memento.Name: Memento
Memento.Effects: Memento may be used as a Free Action that does not consume a Command action when the user becomes Fainted. Lower each of the target's stats by -2 CS.

Nasty Plot.Name: Nasty Plot
Nasty Plot.Effects: Raise the user's Special Attack by +2 CS.

Night Daze.Name: Night Daze
Night Daze.Effects: Night Daze lowers the target's Accuracy by -1 on 13+.

Night Slash.Name: Night Slash
Night Slash.Effects: Night Slash is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Parting Shot.Name: Parting Shot
Parting Shot.Effects: If Parting Shot successfully hits, the target's Attack and Special Attack stats are lowered by one CS and the user is immediately recalled in the same turn. A new Pokemon may immediately be sent out. using Parting Shot lets a Trapped user be recalled.

Payback.Name: Payback
Payback.Effects: If the target hit the user with a Damaging Move on the previous turn, Payback has a Damage Base of 10 (3d8+10 / 24) instead.

Power Trip.Name: Power Trip
Power Trip.Effects: This Move gains +2 to its Damage Base for every positive Combat Stage held by the user, to a maximum of DB20.

Punishment.Name: Punishment
Punishment.Effects: Punishment's Damage Base is raised by +1 for each Combat Stage the target has, to a maximum of DB 12.

Pursuit.Name: Pursuit
Pursuit.Effects: If the foe is fleeing or being switched out, Pursuit may be used as an Interrupt, targeting the triggering foe. When used as an Interrupt, Pursuit grants the user a +5 bonus to all Movement Speeds, and has a Damage Base of 8 (2d8+10/19).

Quash.Name: Quash
Quash.Effects: Change the target's Initiative to 0 for the remainder of the round.

Snarl.Name: Snarl
Snarl.Effects: Lower the Special Attack of all legal targets by -1 CS.

Snatch.Name: Snatch
Snatch.Effects: If the target uses a Self-Targeting Move, you may use Snatch as an Interrupt. You gain the benefits of the Self-Targeting Move instead of the target.

Sucker Punch.Name: Sucker Punch
Sucker Punch.Effects: If an adjacent foe targets the user with a Damaging Attack, Sucker Punch may be used as an Interrupt Move against the triggering foe.

Switcheroo.Name: Switcheroo
Switcheroo.Effects: The user and the target exchange held items.

Thief.Name: Thief
Thief.Effects: Thief takes the target's held item and attaches it to Thief's user if the user is not holding anything.

Throat Chop.Name: Throat Chop
Throat Chop.Effects: The target cannot use Moves with the Sonic keyword for the next two turns.

Topsy-Turvy.Name: Topsy-Turvy
Topsy-Turvy.Effects: The target’s Combat Stages are inverted; +1 Stage becomes -1 Stage, -3 Stages becomes +3 Stages, etc.

Clanging Scales.Name: Clanging Scales
Clanging Scales.Effects: The user adds half their Defense Stat to Clanging Scale's Damage Roll. After the Move is resolved, the user's Defense is lowered by 1 CS.

Draco Meteor.Name: Draco Meteor
Draco Meteor.Effects: Lower the user's Special Attack by -2 CS after damage.

Dragon Dance.Name: Dragon Dance
Dragon Dance.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack and Speed by +1 CS.

Dragon Rage.Name: Dragon Rage
Dragon Rage.Effects: Dragon Rage causes the target to lose 15 HP. Dragon Rage is Special and interacts with other moves and effects as such (Special Evasion may be applied to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc.).

Dragon Rush.Name: Dragon Rush
Dragon Rush.Effects: The target is Pushed 3 Meters. Dragon Rush Flinches the target on 17+.

Dragon Tail.Name: Dragon Tail
Dragon Tail.Effects: The target is Pushed 6 meters minus their Weight Class. The target is also Tripped on 15+.

Dragon Breath.Name: Dragon Breath
Dragon Breath.Effects: Dragon Breath Paralyzes the target on 15+.

Outrage.Name: Outrage
Outrage.Effects: Outrage makes the user becomes Enraged and Confused after damage is dealt.

Roar of Time.Name: Roar of Time
Roar of Time.Effects: Roar of Time Slows all legal targets, even if the attack misses.

Spacial Rend.Name: Spacial Rend
Spacial Rend.Effects: Spacial Rend is a Critical Hit on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Twister.Name: Twister
Twister.Effects: Twister Flinches the target on 18+. Small or Medium targets in the central square of the blast are not hit. Any Pokémon Airborne as a result of Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop above the Blast are hit, ignoring range, and Twister has a Damage Base of 8 against those targets instead.

Bolt Strike.Name: Bolt Strike
Bolt Strike.Effects: Bolt Strike Paralyzes the target on 17+.

Charge.Name: Charge
Charge.Effects: If the user performs an Electric Attack on its next turn, add its Damage Dice Roll an extra time to the damage. Raise the user's Special Defense by +1 CS.

Charge Beam.Name: Charge Beam
Charge Beam.Effects: If Charge Beam successfully hits a target, roll 1d20. On a roll of 7+, the user's Special Attack is raised by +1 Combat Stage.

Discharge.Name: Discharge
Discharge.Effects: Discharge Paralyzes all legal targets on 15+.

Eerie Impulse.Name: Eerie Impulse
Eerie Impulse.Effects: Lower the target's Special Attack by -2 CS. *Grants Glow.

Electric Terrain.Name: Electric Terrain
Electric Terrain.Effects: The field becomes Electrified for 5 rounds. While the field is Electrified, Pokemon and Trainers touching the ground are immune to Sleep, and Electric-Type attacks used by Pokemon and Trainers touching the ground gain a +10 Bonus to Damage Rolls.

Electrify.Name: Electrify
Electrify.Effects: Until the end of the user's next turn, the target's damaging Water-Type attacks and Melee attacks of any Type deal Electric-Type Damage instead of their usual Type.

Electro Ball.Name: Electro Ball
Electro Ball.Effects: When determining the damage dealt by Electro Ball, the user adds its Speed Stat (including CS) in addition to their Special Attack Stat. The target in turn subtracts both its Speed and Special Defense Stats from the damage dealt before applying Type Effectiveness.

Electroweb.Name: Electroweb
Electroweb.Effects: Lower the Speed of all legal targets by -1 CS.

Fusion Bolt.Name: Fusion Bolt
Fusion Bolt.Effects: Fusion Bolt has its Damage Base increased by +3 if Fusion Flare was used this round or last round by any participant of the encounter.

Ion Deluge.Name: Ion Deluge
Ion Deluge.Effects: An ion cloud is dispersed in the targeted area. All Normal-Type Moves targeting into or originating from the area become Electric-Type Moves.

Magnet Rise.Name: Magnet Rise
Magnet Rise.Effects: The user gains the Levitate Ability for 5 turns. Magnet Rise may be activated as a Swift Action if the user is otherwise given an action that consumes a Command.

Magnetic Flux.Name: Magnetic Flux
Magnetic Flux.Effects: Raise the Defense and Special Defense of all legal targets with the Minus or Plus Abilities by +1 CS.

Parabolic Charge.Name: Parabolic Charge
Parabolic Charge.Effects: The user gains HP equal to half of the total damage the user dealt to all legal targets.

Thunder.Name: Thunder
Thunder.Effects: Thunder Paralyzes the target on 15+. If the target is in Sunny Weather, Thunder's Accuracy Check is 11. If the target is in Rainy Weather, Thunder cannot miss. If the target is airborne as a result of Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop, Thunder cannot miss.

Thunder Fang.Name: Thunder Fang
Thunder Fang.Effects: Thunder Fang Paralyzes or Flinches on 18-19; flip a coin to determine whether the foe becomes Paralyzed or Flinched. On 20, the foe is both Paralyzed and Flinched.

Thunder Punch.Name: Thunder Punch
Thunder Punch.Effects: Thunder Punch Paralyzes the target on 19+.

Thunder Shock.Name: Thunder Shock
Thunder Shock.Effects: Thunder Shock Paralyzes the target on 17+. *Grants Zapper

Thunder Wave.Name: Thunder Wave
Thunder Wave.Effects: Thunder Wave cannot miss. Thunder Wave Paralyzes the target. Pokémon immune to Electric Attacks are immune to Thunder Wave's effects.

Volt Switch.Name: Volt Switch
Volt Switch.Effects: If Volt Switch successfully hits its target, the user deals damage and then immediately is returned to its Poke Ball in the same turn. A New Pokemon may immediately be sent out. Using Volt Switch lets a Trapped user be recalled

Volt Tackle.Name: Volt Tackle
Volt Tackle.Effects: Volt Tackle Paralyzes the target on 19+.

Zap Cannon.Name: Zap Cannon
Zap Cannon.Effects: Zap Cannon Paralyzes the target. Zap Cannon ignores the target's Evasion if their are no other combatants or Rough or Blocking Terrain within 2 meters of the target.

Zing Zap.Name: Zing Zap
Zing Zap.Effects: Zing Zap Flinches the target on 15+.

Aromatic Mist.Name: Aromatic Mist
Aromatic Mist.Effects: Raise the Special Defense of all allied legal targets by +1 CS.

Baby-Doll Eyes.Name: Baby-Doll Eyes
Baby-Doll Eyes.Effects: Lower the target's Attack by -1 CS.

Charm.Name: Charm
Charm.Effects: Lower the target’s Attack by -2 CS.

Crafty Shield.Name: Crafty Shield
Crafty Shield.Effects: If the user or an Ally within 2 meters of Crafty Shield's user is hit by a Status Move, you may use Crafty Shield as an Interrupt. All targets in Crafty Shield's area-of-effect including the user, are instead not hit by the triggering Move and do not suffer any of its effects.

Draining Kiss.Name: Draining Kiss
Draining Kiss.Effects: The user gains HP equal to half of the damage the user dealt to the target.

Fairy Lock.Name: Fairy Lock
Fairy Lock.Effects: All legal targets become Trapped and Slowed while the user remains in the encounter. If the user is switched or knocked out, this effect ends.

Fleur Cannon.Name: Fleur Cannon
Fleur Cannon.Effects: Lower the user’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages after damage.

Floral Healing.Name: Floral Healing
Floral Healing.Effects: The target recovers 1/2 their maximum Hit Points. If the Field is Grassy Terrain, the target instead recovers 2/3 their maximum Hit Points.

Flower Shield.Name: Flower Shield
Flower Shield.Effects: Raise the Defense of all Grass-Type legal targets by +2 CS.

Geomancy.Name: Geomancy
Geomancy.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user may not shift this round. The user may create as many squares of Rough Terrain as it wants within a Burst 3 as plants burst through the ground, regardless of the surface material. Resolution Effect: Geomancy raises the user's Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed by +2 CS.

Sweet Kiss.Name: Sweet Kiss
Sweet Kiss.Effects: The target is Confused. On miss, the target suffers a -2 penalty to Accuracy Rolls for one full round.

Misty Terrain.Name: Misty Terrain
Misty Terrain.Effects: The area becomes Misty for 5 turns, While Misty, all Pokemon and Traners standing on the ground ignore the first turn of all Status Afflictions, and Dragon-type attacks targeting or origination from a grounded Pokemon or Trainer take a -10 Penalty to Damage Rolls.

Moonblast.Name: Moonblast
Moonblast.Effects: Moonblast lowers the target’s Special Attack by -1 CS on 15+.

Moonlight.Name: Moonlight
Moonlight.Effects: The user regains HP equal to half of its full HP. If it is Sunny, the user gains 2/3 of its full HP. If it is Rainy, Sand Storming, or Hailing, the user gains 1/4 of its full HP.

Nature's Madness.Name: Nature's Madness
Nature's Madness.Effects: The target loses half of their current Hit Points.

Play Rough.Name: Play Rough
Play Rough.Effects: Play Rough lowers the target’s Attack by -1 CS on 17+.

Brick Break.Name: Brick Break
Brick Break.Effects: Light Screen and Reflect may not be activated in response to Brick Break.

Bulk Up.Name: Bulk Up
Bulk Up.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack and Defense by +1 CS each.

Circle Throw.Name: Circle Throw
Circle Throw.Effects: The target is Pushed 6 meters minus their Weight Class. The target is also Tripped on 15+.

Close Combat.Name: Close Combat
Close Combat.Effects: Lower the user’s Defense and Special Defense by -1 CS each after damage.

Counter.Name: Counter
Counter.Effects: Counter may be used as a Reaction when the user is hit by a damaging Physical Attack. Resolve the Triggering Attack, with Counter's user resisting the attack one step further. After the attack is resolved, if Counter's user was not Fainted, the triggering foe then loses Hit Points equal to twice the amount of Hit Points lost by the user from the triggering attack. Note that Counter is Physical, and while it cannot miss, it cannot hit targets immune to Fighting-Type Moves.

Cross Chop.Name: Cross Chop
Cross Chop.Effects: Cross Chop is a Critical Hit on 16+.

Detect.Name: Detect
Detect.Effects: If the user is hit by a Move, the user may use Detect. The user is instead not hit by the Move. You do not take any damage nor are you affected by anty of the Move's effects

Drain Punch.Name: Drain Punch
Drain Punch.Effects: After the target takes damage, the user gains HP equal to half of the damage it dealt to the target.

Dynamic Punch.Name: Dynamic Punch
Dynamic Punch.Effects: Dynamic Punch Confuses the target. Dynamic Punch ignores the target's Evasion if they are Flanked.

Final Gambit.Name: Final Gambit
Final Gambit.Effects: Final Gambit lowers the user to 0 Hit Points and causes them to Faint. Final Gambit then deals 1 point of damage to the target for every Hit Point lost by the user. Final Gambit does not cause items to activate.

Flying Press.Name: Flying Press
Flying Press.Effects: Flying Press may deal Flying Type damage if the user wishes. NOTE: If Flying Press is Move Sync'd, it only changes the Fighting Type portion of the Move. You can still only choose between that Type and Flying Type; you cannot shift Flying Press to change the Flying part to another Type.

Focus Blast.Name: Focus Blast
Focus Blast.Effects: Focus Blast lowers the target's Special Defense by -1 CS on 18+.

Focus Punch.Name: Focus Punch
Focus Punch.Effects: Use of Focus Punch must be declared as a Priority (Limited) action at the beginning of the round. Nothing happens at this time. At the end of the round, if the target hasn't been hit by an attack dealing damage equal to at least 25% of the user's Maximum Hit Points, the user may Shift and use Focus Punch. Focus Punch's Frequency is not expended if it is negated by an attack.

Force Palm.Name: Force Palm
Force Palm.Effects: Force Palm Paralyzes the target on 18+.

Hammer Arm.Name: Hammer Arm
Hammer Arm.Effects: The user lowers their Speed by -1 CS.

High Jump Kick.Name: High Jump Kick
High Jump Kick.Effects: If High Jump Kick misses, the user loses Hit Points equal to 1/4th of their Max Hit Points. A failure to hit due to a Move with the Shield keyword does not count as a miss. This cannot be used if Gravity is in effect.

Jump Kick.Name: Jump Kick
Jump Kick.Effects: If Jump Kick misses, the user loses Hit Points equal to 1/4th of their Max Hit Points. A failure to hit due to a Move with the Shield keyword does not count as a miss. This cannot be used if Gravity is in effect.

Karate Chop.Name: Karate Chop
Karate Chop.Effects: Karate Chop is a Critical Hit on 17+.

Low Kick.Name: Low Kick
Low Kick.Effects: Low Kick's Damage Base is equal to twice the target's Weight Class.

Low Sweep.Name: Low Sweep
Low Sweep.Effects: Lower the target’s Speed by -1 CS.

Mat Block.Name: Mat Block
Mat Block.Effects: If the user or an adjacent ally is hit by a damagin attack, the user may use Mat Block. The attack instead does not hit any targets, and it deals no damage and has no effects. You may only use Mat Block during the first round of an encounter

Power-Up Punch.Name: Power-Up Punch
Power-Up Punch.Effects: If Power-Up Punch successfully hits a target, the user's Attack is raised by +1 Combat Stage

Quick Guard.Name: Quick Guard
Quick Guard.Effects: If the user or an adjacent ally is targeted by a Priority or Interrupt Attack, Quick Guard may be declared as an Interrupt, causing the triggering attack to have no effect.

Revenge.Name: Revenge
Revenge.Effects: When declaring Revenge, the user does nothing and may not Shift. At the end of the round, the user may Shift and use Revenge. If the target damaged the user this round, Revenge has a Damage Base of 12 (4d10+15 / 40).

Reversal.Name: Reversal
Reversal.Effects: For each Injury the user has, Reversal's Damage Base is increased by +1.

Rock Smash.Name: Rock Smash
Rock Smash.Effects: Rock Smash lowers the target’s Defense 1 Combat Stage on 17+.

Rolling Kick.Name: Rolling Kick
Rolling Kick.Effects: Rolling Kick Flinches the target on 15+.

Secret Sword.Name: Secret Sword
Secret Sword.Effects: When calculating damage, the target subtracts their Defense from Secret Sword's damage instead of their Special Defense. Psyshock is still otherwise Special (Special Evasion is used to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc.)

Seismic Toss.Name: Seismic Toss
Seismic Toss.Effects: The target loses HP equal to the level of Seismic Toss's user. Do not apply weakness or resistance. Do not apply stats.

Sky Uppercut.Name: Sky Uppercut
Sky Uppercut.Effects: Sky Uppercut may be used as an Interrupt when against a target initiating Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop. If Sky Uppercut successfully hits its target, the Triggering Move fails (though the target may take their next turn normally.)

Storm Throw.Name: Storm Throw
Storm Throw.Effects: If Storm Throw hits, it is a Critical Hit.

Submission.Name: Submission
Submission.Effects: On an accuracy roll of 15+, the target is Tripped.

Superpower.Name: Superpower
Superpower.Effects: Superpower lowers the user's Attack and Defense by 1 Combat Stage each.

Triple Kick.Name: Triple Kick
Triple Kick.Effects: Make three attacks with Triple Kick. If you hit once, Triple Kick has a DB of 1. If you hit two times, Triple Kick has a DB of 3. If you hit three times, Triple Kick has a DB of 6.

Vital Throw.Name: Vital Throw
Vital Throw.Effects: If the user is targeted by a Melee attack and has not yet taken a turn this round, the user may declare Vital Throw. After the triggering attack is resolved, the user may use Vital Throw against the triggering foe as a Reaction. Vital Throw cannot miss.

Wake-Up Slap.Name: Wake-Up Slap
Wake-Up Slap.Effects: If the target is Asleep, Wake-Up Slap has a Damage Base of 10 (3d8+10 / 24) instead, and cures the target of Sleep.

Blaze Kick.Name: Blaze Kick
Blaze Kick.Effects: Blaze Kick Burns the target on 19+ and is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Blue Flare.Name: Blue Flare
Blue Flare.Effects: Blue Flare Burns the target on 17+.

Burn Up.Name: Burn Up
Burn Up.Effects: Until the end of the encounter, the user loses its Fire-Type (pure Fire-Types become Normal-Type).

Ember.Name: Ember
Ember.Effects: Ember Burns the target on 18+. *Grants: Firestarter

Eruption.Name: Eruption
Eruption.Effects: For each 10% of HP the user is missing, Eruption's Damage Base is reduced by 1. Eruption creates a 1 meter burst, but also affects an area 10 meters tall straight up.

Fiery Dance.Name: Fiery Dance
Fiery Dance.Effects: If Fiery Dance successfully hits a foe, it raises the user's Special Attack by 1 Combat Stage on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Fire Blast.Name: Fire Blast
Fire Blast.Effects: Fire Blast burns the target on 19+.

Fire Fang.Name: Fire Fang
Fire Fang.Effects: Fire Fang Burns or Flinches on 18-19 during Accuracy Check; flip a coin to determine whether the foe becomes Burned or Flinched. On 20 during Accuracy Check, the foe is both Burned and Flinched.

Fire Lash.Name: Fire Lash
Fire Lash.Effects: The target's Defense is lowered by -1 CS.

Fire Pledge.Name: Fire Pledge
Fire Pledge.Effects: If an ally uses Grass Pledge or Water Pledge, you may use Fire Pledge as Priority (Advanced) immediately after their turn to target the same foe. If used in conjunction with Grass Pledge, Fire Hazards are created in a Brust 1 around the target. If used in conjucntion with Water Pledge, a Rainbow is created that lasts for 5 rouns. Counsult the Pledge keyword for additional details.

Fire Punch.Name: Fire Punch
Fire Punch.Effects: Fire Punch Burns the target on 19+.

Fire Spin.Name: Fire Spin
Fire Spin.Effects: The target is put in a Vortex. *Grants: Firestarter

Flame Burst.Name: Flame Burst
Flame Burst.Effects: Any Trainers or Pokémon cardinally adjacent to the target lose 5 Hit Points

Flame Charge.Name: Flame Charge
Flame Charge.Effects: Raise the user’s Speed 1 Combat Stage.

Flame Wheel.Name: Flame Wheel
Flame Wheel.Effects: Flame Wheel Burns the target on 19+.

Flare Blitz.Name: Flare Blitz
Flare Blitz.Effects: Flare Blitz Burns the target on 19+.

Fusion Flare.Name: Fusion Flare
Fusion Flare.Effects: If Fusion Bolt was used this round or last round by any participant of the encounter, Fusion Flare has its Damage Base increased by +3.

Heat Crash.Name: Heat Crash
Heat Crash.Effects: For each weight class the user is above the target, increase Heavy Crash's damage base by +2.

Heat Wave.Name: Heat Wave
Heat Wave.Effects: Heat Wave Burns all Legal Targets on 18+.

Incinerate.Name: Incinerate
Incinerate.Effects: If a target is holding a Held Item or Main or Off-Hand item, they must either drop it immediately or lose a Tick of Hit Points. This may only cause a target to lose at most one Tick of Hit Points, no matter how many items they were holding

Inferno.Name: Inferno
Inferno.Effects: Inferno Burns the target. Inferno ignores the target's Evasion if there are no other combatants or Rough or Blocking Terrain within 2 meters of the target.

Lava Plume.Name: Lava Plume
Lava Plume.Effects: Lava Plume burns all targets on 16+.

Magma Storm.Name: Magma Storm
Magma Storm.Effects: The target is put in a Vortex; this effect occurs even if Magma Storm misses its target.

Mystical Fire.Name: Mystical Fire
Mystical Fire.Effects: Mystical Fire lowers the target’s Special Attack by 1 Combat Stage.

Overheat.Name: Overheat
Overheat.Effects: Lower the user's Special Attack 2 Combat Stages after damage.

Sacred Fire.Name: Sacred Fire
Sacred Fire.Effects: Sacred Fire Burns the target on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Searing Shot.Name: Searing Shot
Searing Shot.Effects: Searing Shot Burns all targets on 15+.

Shell Trap.Name: Shell Trap
Shell Trap.Effects: If the user is hit by a Melee attack, they may use Shell Trap as an Interrupt.

Sunny Day.Name: Sunny Day
Sunny Day.Effects: The weather becomes Sunny for 5 rounds. While Sunny, Fire-Type Attacks gain a +5 bonus to Damage Rolls, and Water-Type Attacks suffer a -5 Damage penalty.

V-Create.Name: V-Create
V-Create.Effects: Lowers the user's Defense, Special Defense, and Speed by -1 CS each.

Acrobatics.Name: Acrobatics
Acrobatics.Effects: If the user is not holding an item, Acrobatics instead has a Damage Base of 11 (3d10+10/27)

Aeroblast.Name: Aeroblast
Aeroblast.Effects: Aeroblast is a Critical Hit on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Air Cutter.Name: Air Cutter
Air Cutter.Effects: Air Cutter is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Air Slash.Name: Air Slash
Air Slash.Effects: Air Slash Flinches the target on 15+.

Beak Blast.Name: Beak Blast
Beak Blast.Effects: Beak Blast must be declared at the start of the round. If the user is hit by a Melee attack this round, the triggering attacker is Burned. At the end of the round, the user Shifts and attacks with Beak Blast.

Bounce.Name: Bounce
Bounce.Effects: The user first Shifts, gaining a +1 Bonus to Movement Speed and to their Jump Capabilities. After the user Shifts, they may attack with Bounce. The target becomes Vulnerable, and is Paralyzed on 16+. Grants High Jump +1

Brave Bird.Name: Brave Bird
Brave Bird.Effects: The target is pushed back 2 meters.

Defog.Name: Defog
Defog.Effects: The Weather becomes Clear, and all Blessings, Coats, and Hazards are destroyed. Clear Weather is the default weather, conferring no bonuses or penalties of any sort.

Dragon Ascent.Name: Dragon Ascent
Dragon Ascent.Effects: The user’s Defense and Special Defense are each lowered by -1 Combat Stage.

Feather Dance.Name: Feather Dance
Feather Dance.Effects: All legal targets have their Attack lowered 2 Combat Stages.

Fly.Name: Fly
Fly.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user is moved up 25 meters into the air. Resolution Effect: The user may shift twice while in the air, using their overland or sky speed, and then comes down next to a legal target, and attacks with Fly. *Grants: Sky +3

Gust.Name: Gust
Gust.Effects: If the target is airborne as a result of Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop, Gust can hit them, ignoring Range and has a Damage Base of 8 instead. *Grants: Guster

Hurricane.Name: Hurricane
Hurricane.Effects: Hurricane Confuses its target on 15+. If the target is in Sunny Weather, Hurricane's Accuracy Check is 11. If the target is in Rainy Weather, Hurricane cannot miss. If the target is airborne as a result of Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop, Hurricane cannot miss.

Mirror Move.Name: Mirror Move
Mirror Move.Effects: Use the Move the target has used on their last turn. You may choose new targets for the Move. Mirror Move cannot miss.

Oblivion Wing.Name: Oblivion Wing
Oblivion Wing.Effects: The user gains HP equal to Oblivion Wing’s Damage Roll.

Pluck.Name: Pluck
Pluck.Effects: Pluck takes the target's Held Item or Accessory Slot Item and attaches it to Pluck's user, if the user is not holding anything.

Roost.Name: Roost
Roost.Effects: The user regains HP equal to half of its full HP. If the user is a Flying Type, it loses the Flying Type until the start of their next turn.

Sky Attack.Name: Sky Attack
Sky Attack.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user is moved up 25 meters into the air. Resolution Effect: The user may shift until they are next to a legal target in the encounter. They may then shift again and pass through legal targets to attack with Sky Attack. Sky Attack Flinches a target on 17+.

Sky Drop.Name: Sky Drop
Sky Drop.Effects: Set-Up Effect: Make Sky Drop's Accuracy Check. If the user hits, the user and target are moved 25 meters into the air. The target forfeits their next turn and cannot Shift or take actions until Sky Drop is resolved. Resolution Effect: Shift while in the air and lower both the user and the target heights back to the ground. Then apply Sky Drop's damage. If the target has a Sky or Levitate Speed, Sky Drop fails to deal damage. If the user is Fainted after the Set-Up but before the Resolution, the target falls to the ground and takes damage as if Sky Drop had a Damage Base of 3 (1d6+5/8) unless they have a Sky or Levitate Speed, in which case they take no damage.

Tailwind.Name: Tailwind
Tailwind.Effects: For the remainder of the encounter, all allied trainers and Pokémon gain +5 to their Initiative. Multiple instances of Tailwind cannot stack. *Grants: Guster

Astonish.Name: Astonish
Astonish.Effects: Astonish Flinches the target on 15+. Once per Scene, if the target is unaware of the user's presence, Astonish automatically Flinches.

Curse.Name: Curse
Curse.Effects: If the user is not a Ghost Type, Curse has a Frequency of EOT, and when used the user lowers its Speed by -1 Combat Stage, but raises Attack and Defense by +1 Combat Stage each. If the user is a Ghost Type, Curse has a Frequency of Scene, and when used the user loses 1/3 of their Max Hit Points and a target Pokémon or Trainer within 8 meters of the user becomes Cursed. This Hit Point loss cannot be prevented in any way.

Destiny Bond.Name: Destiny Bond
Destiny Bond.Effects: All enemy targets in the burst become Bound to the user until the end of your next turn. If a Bound target causes the user to Faint through a Damaging Attack, the Bound target immediately faints after their attack is resolved.

Grudge.Name: Grudge
Grudge.Effects: You may use Grudge as an Interrupt when a Damaging Attack causes the user to faint. Grudge is activated as a Free Action (does not take up a Command.) The attack is resolved as usual, and the user Faints. The attacker that caused the user to Faint becomes Suppressed for the remainder of the encounter; switching and Taking a Breather does not end Suppression when used this way.

Hex.Name: Hex
Hex.Effects: Once a Scene, if Hex's target has a Status Affliction, you may have Hex's Damage Base be 13 instead (4d10+10 / 35)

Moongeist Beam.Name: Moongeist Beam
Moongeist Beam.Effects: This Move ignores any Abilities that would cause it to fail or miss; those Abilities cannot be activated in response to Moongeist Beam (ex: Dodge, Wonder Guard)

Night Shade.Name: Night Shade
Night Shade.Effects: The target loses HP equal to the level of Night Shade's user. Do not apply weakness or resistance. Do not apply stats.

Nightmare.Name: Nightmare
Nightmare.Effects: Nightmare can only hit Legal Targets that are Asleep. The target gains Bad Sleep.

Ominous Wind.Name: Ominous Wind
Ominous Wind.Effects: The user has each of its stats raised by +1 CS on a 19+.

Phantom Force.Name: Phantom Force
Phantom Force.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user is removed from the field, and their turn ends. Resolution Effect: Phantom Force’s user appears adjacent to any legal target on the field, ignoring Movement Capabilities, and then uses Phantom Force’s attack. Phantom Force cannot be avoided by Moves with the Shield Keyword, the Dodge Ability, or similar effects, and Intercepts may not be attempted in response.

Shadow Ball.Name: Shadow Ball
Shadow Ball.Effects: Shadow Ball lowers the target's Special Defense by -1 CS on 17+.

Shadow Bone.Name: Shadow Bone
Shadow Bone.Effects: Lower the target's Defense by -1 CS on a 17+. Counts as a Bone Move for Cubone/Marowak’s Abilities, etc.

Shadow Claw.Name: Shadow Claw
Shadow Claw.Effects: Shadow Claw is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Shadow Force.Name: Shadow Force
Shadow Force.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user is removed from the field, and their turn ends. Resolution Effect: Shadow Force’s user appears adjacent to any legal target on the field, ignoring Movement Capabilities, and then uses Shadow Force’s attack. Shadow Force cannot be avoided by Moves with the Shield Keyword, the Dodge Ability, or similar effects, and Intercepts may not be attempted in response.

Spectral Thief.Name: Spectral Thief
Spectral Thief.Effects: Before rolling damage, transfer all Combat Stages on the target to the user.

Spirit Shackle.Name: Spirit Shackle
Spirit Shackle.Effects: The Target is Trapped for 2 rounds.

Spite.Name: Spite
Spite.Effects: Spite may be used as a Free Action that does not take up a Command whenever the user is hit by a Move. That Move becomes Disabled for the attacker.

Trick-or-Treat.Name: Trick-or-Treat
Trick-or-Treat.Effects: The target gains the Ghost Type in addition to its other Types for 5 turns.

Absorb.Name: Absorb
Absorb.Effects: After the target takes damage, the user gains HP equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Aromatherapy.Name: Aromatherapy
Aromatherapy.Effects: All allies in the burst are cured of one status condition of their choice.

Cotton Guard.Name: Cotton Guard
Cotton Guard.Effects: Raise the user’s Defense 3 Combat Stages.

Cotton Spore.Name: Cotton Spore
Cotton Spore.Effects: All legal targets have their Speed lowered 2 Combat Stages.

Energy Ball.Name: Energy Ball
Energy Ball.Effects: Energy Ball lowers the foe’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage on 17+.

Forest's Curse.Name: Forest's Curse
Forest's Curse.Effects: The target gains the Grass Type in addition to its other Types for 5 turns.

Giga Drain.Name: Giga Drain
Giga Drain.Effects: After the target takes damage, the user gains HP equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Grass Knot.Name: Grass Knot
Grass Knot.Effects: Grass Knot's Damage Base is equal to twice the target's Weight Class.

Grass Pledge.Name: Grass Pledge
Grass Pledge.Effects: If an ally uses Fire Pledge or Water Pledge, you may use Grass Pledge as Priority (Advanced) immediately after their turn to target the same foe. If used in conjunction with Fire Pledge, Fire Hazards are created in a Burst 1 around the target. If used in conjunction with Water Pledge, the target and all foes adjacent to the the target are slowed and have their Speed reduced by 2 Combat Stages. Consult the Pledge keyword for additional details.

Grassy Terrain.Name: Grassy Terrain
Grassy Terrain.Effects: The area becomes Grassy for 5 rounds. While Grassy, all Pokémon and Trainers standing on the ground recover 1/10th of their maximum Hit Points at the start of every turn, and Grass-Type attacks performed by grounded Pokémon and Trainers gain a +10 bonus to Damage Rolls.

Horn Leech.Name: Horn Leech
Horn Leech.Effects: After the target takes damage, the user gains HP equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Ingrain.Name: Ingrain
Ingrain.Effects: Ingrain applies a Coat to the user, which has the following effect; the user cannot be pushed or pulled, and cannot be switched out. At the beginning of each of the user's turn, the user gains HP equal to 1/10th of its max HP.

Leaf Blade.Name: Leaf Blade
Leaf Blade.Effects: Leaf Blade is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Leaf Storm.Name: Leaf Storm
Leaf Storm.Effects: Lower the user’s Special Attack 2 Combat Stages after damage.

Leaf Tornado.Name: Leaf Tornado
Leaf Tornado.Effects: Small or Medium targets in the central square of the blast are not hit. On 15+, all legal targets have their Accuracy lowered by -1.

Leech Seed.Name: Leech Seed
Leech Seed.Effects: At the beginning of each of the target's turns, Leech Seed's target loses 1/10th of their full HP. Leech Seed's user then gains HP equal to the amount the target lost. Leech Seed lasts until the target faints or is returned to a Poké Ball. Grass Types and targets immune to Grass Attacks are immune to Leech Seed

Mega Drain.Name: Mega Drain
Mega Drain.Effects: After the target takes damage, the user gains HP equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target.

Needle Arm.Name: Needle Arm
Needle Arm.Effects: Needle Arm Flinches the target on 15+.

Petal Dance.Name: Petal Dance
Petal Dance.Effects: After damage is dealt, the user becomes Enraged and Confused.

Razor Leaf.Name: Razor Leaf
Razor Leaf.Effects: Razor Leaf is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Seed Flare.Name: Seed Flare
Seed Flare.Effects: All Legal Targets have their Special Defense lowered 1 Combat Stage.

Solar Beam.Name: Solar Beam
Solar Beam.Effects: Set-Up Effect: If the weather is not Sunny, the user’s turn ends. If the weather is Sunny, immediately proceed to the Resolution Effect instead and this Move loses the Set-Up keyword. Resolution Effect: The user attacks with Solar Beam. If the weather is Rainy, Sandstorming, or Hailing, Solar Beam’s Damage Base is lowered to 6 (2d6+8 / 15).

Solar Blade.Name: Solar Blade
Solar Blade.Effects: Set-Up Effect: If the weather is not Sunny, the user’s gains +1 Attack CS and +1 Special Defense CS. If it is Sunny, immediately Resolve. Resolution Effect: Attack with Solar Blade. Half damage in Sandstorm, Hail, or Rain.

Spiky Shield.Name: Spiky Shield
Spiky Shield.Effects: If the user is hit by an attack, the user may use Spiky Shield. The user is instead not hit by the Move. You do not take any damage nor are you affected by any of the Move’s effects. In addition, if the triggering attack was Melee-ranged, the attacker loses Hit Points equal to 1/10th of their Max Hit Points.

Strength Sap.Name: Strength Sap
Strength Sap.Effects: The user gains Hit Points equal to the higher of the target's Attack or Special Attack; the target then loses -1 CS in that Stat.

Synthesis.Name: Synthesis
Synthesis.Effects: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value. If it is Sunny, the user gains 2/3 of its full Hit Point value. If it is Rainy, Sand Storming, or Hailing, the user gains 1/4 of its full Hit Point value.

Trop Kick.Name: Trop Kick
Trop Kick.Effects: The target receives a -5 penalty to damage rolls for 1 round.

Worry Seed.Name: Worry Seed
Worry Seed.Effects: You choose one of the target’s Abilities. Worry Seed changes that Ability to Insomnia for the remainder of the encounter.

Bone Club.Name: Bone Club
Bone Club.Effects: Bone Club Flinches the target on 18+.

Bulldoze.Name: Bulldoze
Bulldoze.Effects: All Legal Targets are lowered 1 Speed Combat Stage.

Dig.Name: Dig
Dig.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user shifts 25 meters underground and their turn ends. Resolution Effect: The user may shift horizontally using their burrow or overland speed, and then shifts 25 meters straight up. Upon reaching the surface, the user attacks with Dig, creating a Burst 1. *Grants: Burrow +3

Drill Run.Name: Drill Run
Drill Run.Effects: Drill Run is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Earth Power.Name: Earth Power
Earth Power.Effects: Earth Power lowers the Special Defense of all Legal Targets 1 Combat Stage on 16+.

Earthquake.Name: Earthquake
Earthquake.Effects: Earthquake can hit targets that are underground, including those using the Move Dig. *Grants Groundshaper

Fissure.Name: Fissure
Fissure.Effects: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User's Level - The Target's Level. *Grants: Groundshaper

High Horsepower.Name: High Horsepower
High Horsepower.Effects: High Horsepower may be used as a Free Action at the end of a Sprint Maneuver taken as a Standard Action, as long as the user Shifted at least 3 meters in a straight line towards the target. When used this way, High Horsepower gains Smite.

Magnitude.Name: Magnitude
Magnitude.Effects: When you use Magnitude, roll 1d6. Magnitude’s Damage Base is equal to 5+X, where X is the value of the d6. Magnitude can hit targets that are underground, including those using the Move Dig. *Grants: Groundshaper

Mud Bomb.Name: Mud Bomb
Mud Bomb.Effects: The target's Accuracy is lowered by -1 on 16+.

Mud Shot.Name: Mud Shot
Mud Shot.Effects: The target's Speed is lowed by -1 Combat Stage.

Mud Sport.Name: Mud Sport
Mud Sport.Effects: All targets in the burst, including the user, gain a Coat which grants them 1 Step of Resistance to Electric Type Moves. After a target has been hit by a damaging Electric Type Move, the coat is removed.

Mud-Slap.Name: Mud-Slap
Mud-Slap.Effects: The target's Accuracy is lowered by -1.

Rototiller.Name: Rototiller
Rototiller.Effects: All Grass-type Pokémon in the area raise their Attack and Special Attack 1 Combat Stage.

Sand Tomb.Name: Sand Tomb
Sand Tomb.Effects: The target is put in a Vortex.

Sand Attack.Name: Sand Attack
Sand Attack.Effects: The target is Blinded until the end of their next turn.

Spikes.Name: Spikes
Spikes.Effects: Set 8 square meters of Spikes within the range such that all 8 meters are adjacent with at least one other space of Spikes. Spikes cause terrain to count as Slow Terrain, and a grounded foe that runs into the hazards will lose 1/10th of their full HP and become Slowed until the end of their next turn.

Stomping Tantrum.Name: Stomping Tantrum
Stomping Tantrum.Effects: If the user’s last attack failed or missed, Stomping Tantrum is DB15 instead.

Aurora Beam.Name: Aurora Beam
Aurora Beam.Effects: Aurora Beam lowers the target's Attack 1 Combat Stage on 18+. *Grants: Freezer

Aurora Veil.Name: Aurora Veil
Aurora Veil.Effects: Blessing – Any user affected by Aurora Veil may activate it when receiving Damage to resist the Damage one step. Aurora Veil may be activated 2 times, and then disappears. Special: Auora Veil can only be used when the user is in Hailing Weather. The Blessings persist even after Hailing Weather has ended, however.

Avalanche.Name: Avalanche
Avalanche.Effects: When declaring Avalanche, the user does nothing and may not Shift. At the end of the round, the user may Shift and use Avalanche. If the target damaged the user this round, Avalanche has a Damage Base of 12 (4d10+15 / 40).

Blizzard.Name: Blizzard
Blizzard.Effects: Blizzard Freezes all legal target on 15+. If the target is in Hailing Weather, Blizzard cannot miss.

Freeze-Dry.Name: Freeze-Dry
Freeze-Dry.Effects: When calculating Weakness and Resistance for Freeze-Dry, Water-Typed targets calculate damage as if Water was weak to Ice.

Freeze Shock.Name: Freeze Shock
Freeze Shock.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user may shift, then ends their turn. Resolution Effect: The user attacks with Freeze Shock. Freeze Shock paralyzes on 15+.

Frost Breath.Name: Frost Breath
Frost Breath.Effects: If Frost Breath hits, it is a Critical Hit. *Grants: Freezer

Glaciate.Name: Glaciate
Glaciate.Effects: All Legal Targets have their Speed lowered 1 Combat Stage. On an Even-Numbered Roll, all Legal Targets on the ground are Slowed.

Hail.Name: Hail
Hail.Effects: The weather changes to Hail for 5 rounds. While it is Hailing, all non-Ice Type Pokemon lose a Tick of Hit Points at the beginning of their turn.

Haze.Name: Haze
Haze.Effects: The Combat Stages of the user and all Pokémon and Trainers in the encounter are set to their default state (usually 0).

Ice Ball.Name: Ice Ball
Ice Ball.Effects: The user continues to use Ice Ball on each of its turns until they miss any target with Ice Ball or are not able to hit any target with Ice Ball during their turn. Each successive use of Ice Ball increases Ice Ball's Damage Base by +3 to a maximum of DB 15.

Ice Burn.Name: Ice Burn
Ice Burn.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user may shift, then ends their turn. Resolution Effect: The user attacks with Ice Burn. Ice Burn Burns on 15+.

Ice Fang.Name: Ice Fang
Ice Fang.Effects: Ice Fang Freezes or Flinches on 18-19 during Accuracy Check; flip a coin to determine whether the foe becomes Frozen or Flinched. On 20 during Accuracy Check, the foe is both Frozen and Flinched.

Ice Hammer.Name: Ice Hammer
Ice Hammer.Effects: Lower the user's Speed by -1 CS.

Ice Punch.Name: Ice Punch
Ice Punch.Effects: Ice Punch Freezes the target on 19+.

Icicle Crash.Name: Icicle Crash
Icicle Crash.Effects: Icicle Crash Flinches the target on 15+.

Icy Wind.Name: Icy Wind
Icy Wind.Effects: All Legal Targets have their Speed lowered 1 Combat Stage.

Mist.Name: Mist
Mist.Effects: Any user affected by Mist may activate it when having Combat Stages lowered by any effect; if they do, those Combat Stages are instead not lowered. Mist may be activated 3 times and then disappears.

Powder Snow.Name: Powder Snow
Powder Snow.Effects: Powder Snow Freezes all Legal Targets on 19+. *Grants: Freezer

Sheer Cold.Name: Sheer Cold
Sheer Cold.Effects: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User's Level - The Target's Level. *Grants: Freezer

Acupressure.Name: Acupressure
Acupressure.Effects: Roll 1d6. On a result of 1, raise the target’s Attack by +2 CS. On a result of 2, raise the target’s Defense by +2 CS. On a result of 3, raise the target’s Special Attack by +2 CS. On a result of 4, raise the target’s Special Defense by +2 CS. On a result of 5, raise the target’s Speed by +2 CS. On a result of 6, raise the target’s Accuracy by +2.

After You.Name: After You
After You.Effects: After You is a Swift Action. The target takes their turn for the round immediately after the user finishes their turn, ignoring Initiative. After You may only affect a target that has not yet acted that round and can only affect willing targets.

Assist.Name: Assist
Assist.Effects: Randomly select another Pokémon on the user’s roster and then randomly select a Move that Pokémon knows. Assist’s user uses that Move immediately.

Attract.Name: Attract
Attract.Effects: Attract Infatuates the target if its gender is the opposite of the user’s. Attract fails when used by or against Genderless targets.

Baton Pass.Name: Baton Pass
Baton Pass.Effects: The user is replaced with another Pokémon from their trainer’s roster. All Combat Stage, Coats, and [Stratagems] on Baton Pass’ user are transferred to the replacement. Baton Pass may be used to switch even if the user is Trapped.

Belly Drum.Name: Belly Drum
Belly Drum.Effects: The user gains +6 Attack CS and loses HP equal to 1/2 of their Max HP.

Bestow.Name: Bestow
Bestow.Effects: The user gives its held item to the target, unless the target is already holding an item. Using Bestow is a Swift Action.

Bide.Name: Bide
Bide.Effects: The user may use Bide as a Reaction Move upon being Hit by a Damaging Move. During their next available turn, the user may Shift and then use Bide, causing all Adjacent foes to lose X HP, where X is the amount of Damage taken since declaring use of Bide (Loss of life through effects such as Poison is not ‘Damage’).

Bind.Name: Bind
Bind.Effects: The user gains a +1 Bonus to Accuracy Rolls made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers, and +2 to Skill Checks made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers or gain Dominance. Whenever the user gains Dominance in a Grapple, the target of the Grapple loses a Tick of Hit Points.

Block.Name: Block
Block.Effects: The target is Stuck and Trapped until the beginning of your next turn.

Body Slam.Name: Body Slam
Body Slam.Effects: Body Slam Paralyzes the target on 15+.

Camouflage.Name: Camouflage
Camouflage.Effects: The user changes their Type to match the field. Forests and grassy areas change the user into a Grass Type. Watery areas change the user into a Water Type. Caves and Mountains could change the user into a Rock or Ground Type. An icy terrain would turn the user into an Ice Type. A building may change the user into a Steel or Normal Type. Weather affects what Type the user becomes. Use common sense; if you are having difficult determining what Type the user should become, consult the GM. *Grants Blender

Captivate.Name: Captivate
Captivate.Effects: Captivate lowers the target's Special Attack by -2 CS. Captivate may not affect something that is the same gender as the user or something that is genderless.

Chip Away.Name: Chip Away
Chip Away.Effects: Ignore any Armor, Damage Reduction, or changes in the target's Defense or Special Defense (such as from Combat Stages) when calculating damage.

Confide.Name: Confide
Confide.Effects: Lower the target's Special Attack by -1 CS.

Constrict.Name: Constrict
Constrict.Effects: Lower the target’s Speed by -1 CS. Constrict may be used as a Swift Action against targets the user is Grappling and automatically hits when performed this way.

Conversion.Name: Conversion
Conversion.Effects: The user becomes the elemental Type of their choice as long as they have a Move that is the same elemental Type until the end of the encounter. Replace all other Types.

Conversion2.Name: Conversion2
Conversion2.Effects: The user becomes the elemental Type of their choice as long as the Type resists the elemental Type of the Move it last took damage from until the end of the encounter. Replace all other Types.

Copycat.Name: Copycat
Copycat.Effects: Use the Move the target has used on their last turn. You may choose new targets for the Move. Copycat cannot miss.

Covet.Name: Covet
Covet.Effects: Covet takes the target’s Held Item or Accessory Slot Item and attaches it to Covet’s user, if the user is not holding anything.

Crush Claw.Name: Crush Claw
Crush Claw.Effects: Crush Claw lowers the target’s Defense by -1 CS on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Crush Grip.Name: Crush Grip
Crush Grip.Effects: For every 10% the target is below their full Hit Points, Crush Grip's Damage Base is reduced by 1.

Cut.Name: Cut
Cut.Effects: Cut ignores up to 5 Damage Reduction (Defenses are not Damage Reduction.)

Defense Curl.Name: Defense Curl
Defense Curl.Effects:
The user becomes Curled Up. While Curled Up, the user becomes immune to Critical Hits and gains 10 Damage Reduction. However, while Curled Up, the user is Slowed and their Accuracy is lowered by -4. The user may stop being Curled Up as a Swift Action. If the user has Rollout or Ice Ball in their Move List, they do not become Slowed while Curled Up. Furthermore, when using the Moves Rollout or Ice Ball while Curled Up, the user gains a +10 bonus to the damage rolls of those Moves and does not suffer Accuracy Penalties from being Curled Up.
September Playtest: The user’s Defense is raised 1 Combat Stage and they become Curled Up until the end of the Scene or they are Recalled or Take a Breather. When using the Moves Rollout or Ice Ball while Curled Up, the user gains a +10 bonus to the damage rolls of those Moves.

Disable.Name: Disable
Disable.Effects: Disable may be used as a Free Action that does not take up a Command whenever the user is hit by a Move. That Move becomes Disabled for the attacker.

Dizzy Punch.Name: Dizzy Punch
Dizzy Punch.Effects: Dizzy Punch Confuses the target on 17+.

Double Team.Name: Double Team
Double Team.Effects: The user gains 3 activations of Double Team. The user may either activate Double Team when being targeted by an attack to increase their Evasion by +2 against that attack or when making an attack to increase their Accuracy by +2 for that attack.

Echoed Voice.Name: Echoed Voice
Echoed Voice.Effects: If Echoed Voice was used by any Pokémon or Trainer in the Encounter on the previous round, increase its Damage Base by +4. If Echoed Voice was used by any Pokémon or Trainers during both the previous two rounds, increase its Damage Base by +8.

Encore.Name: Encore
Encore.Effects: Roll 1d6. On a result of 1 or 2, the target becomes Confused; on a result of 3 or 4 the target becomes Suppressed; on a result of 5 or 6 the target becomes Enraged.

Endeavor.Name: Endeavor
Endeavor.Effects: The target loses a Tick of Hit Points for each Injury the user has.

Endure.Name: Endure
Endure.Effects: If the user is hit by a damaging Move, you may use Endure as a Free Action. If the Move would bring Endure's user down to 0 HP or less, Endure's user instead is set to 1 HP.

Entrainment.Name: Entrainment
Entrainment.Effects: The target gains one of the user's Abilities for 3 turns.

Explosion.Name: Explosion
Explosion.Effects: The user's HP is set to -50% of their full HP. This HP loss cannot be prevented or reduced in any way. The user's loyalty toward its trainer may be lowered.

Facade.Name: Facade
Facade.Effects: If the user is afflicted with a Persistent Status Affliction, Facade's Damage Base is doubled to DB 14 (4d10+15 / 40).

Façade.Name: Façade
Façade.Effects: If the user is afflicted with a Persistent Status Affliction, Façade’s Damage Base is doubled to DB 14 (4d10+15 / 40).

Fake Out.Name: Fake Out
Fake Out.Effects: You may only use Fake Out with Priority upon joining an encounter; if you do, Fake Out Flinches the target. Switching out resets the requirement of joining an encounter.

False Swipe.Name: False Swipe
False Swipe.Effects: False Swipe's damage cannot bring a target lower than 1 HP.

Feint.Name: Feint
Feint.Effects: If a foe uses a Move with the Shield Keyword in response to one of your actions, you may activate Feint to cause the triggering Move to Fail. Feint is activated as a Free Action.

Flail.Name: Flail
Flail.Effects: For each Injury the user has, Flail's Damage Base is increased by +1.

Flash.Name: Flash
Flash.Effects: Lower the Accuracy of all legal targets by -1. *Grants Glow

Focus Energy.Name: Focus Energy
Focus Energy.Effects: The user becomes Pumped. While Pumped, the user's Critical Range is extended by 2, or 18+ if the Critical Range is not otherwise extended. Being switched will cause this effect to end.

Follow Me.Name: Follow Me
Follow Me.Effects: Until the end of the user's next turn, all Foes must target the user when using a Move that targets their opponents. This effect ends if the user is Fainted or Switched out.

Foresight.Name: Foresight
Foresight.Effects: Foresight may be activated as a Swift Action on the user’s turn. For the rest of the turn, the user’s Normal-Type and Fighting-Type Moves can hit and affect Ghost-Type targets, and the user can see through the Illusion Ability, Moves with the Illusion keyword, and effects created by the Illusionist Capability, ignoring all effects from those.

Frustration.Name: Frustration
Frustration.Effects: Frustration's Damage Base is equal to 9 minus the user's Loyalty Value. Using Frustration may make your Pokémon dislike you.

Growl.Name: Growl
Growl.Effects: Lower the Attack of all legal targets by -1 CS.

Growth.Name: Growth
Growth.Effects: Raise the user's Attack and Special Attack by +1 CS each. If it is Sunny, double the amount of Combat Stages gained. *Grants Inflatable

Guillotine.Name: Guillotine
Guillotine.Effects: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User's Level - The Target's Level.

Harden.Name: Harden
Harden.Effects: Raise the user’s Defense by +1 CS.

Head Charge.Name: Head Charge
Head Charge.Effects: The target is Pushed back 2 meters.

Heal Bell.Name: Heal Bell
Heal Bell.Effects: All targets are cured of any Persistent Status ailments.

Helping Hand.Name: Helping Hand
Helping Hand.Effects: Helping Hand grants the target +2 on its next Accuracy Roll this round, and +10 to its next Damage Roll this round.

Hidden Power.Name: Hidden Power
Hidden Power.Effects: When a Pokémon first obtains the Move Hidden Power, roll 1d20. Hidden Power’s Elemental Type will be changed from Normal to Bug on a result of 1; Dark on 2; Dragon on 3; Electric on 4; Fairy on 5; Fighting on 6; Fire on 7; Flying on 8; Ghost on 9; Grass on 10; Ground on 11; Ice on 12; Normal on 13; Poison on 14; Psychic on 15; Rock on 16; Steel on 17; Water on 18; and on 19 or 20, reroll until you roll another number. This effect is permanent – if Hidden Power is forgotten and relearned, the chosen Type remains the same.

Hold Hands.Name: Hold Hands
Hold Hands.Effects:
Both the user and the target become Cheered. They may give up the Cheered condition when making a Save Check to roll twice and take the best result.
September Playtest: The target and the user each gain three Ticks of Temporary Hit Points, and a +2 Bonus to Save Checks for 1 full round.

Horn Drill.Name: Horn Drill
Horn Drill.Effects: Roll 1d100. This roll may not be modified in any way. If you roll X or lower, the target Faints. X is equal to 30 + The User's Level - The Target's Level.

Howl.Name: Howl
Howl.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack by +1 CS.

Hyper Fang.Name: Hyper Fang
Hyper Fang.Effects: Hyper Fang Flinches the target on 19+.

Hyper Voice.Name: Hyper Voice
Hyper Voice.Effects: All legal targets are pushed back to the squares immediately outside the blast, away from the user.

Judgement.Name: Judgement
Judgement.Effects: Judgment's Type can be whatever Elemental Type the user wants it to be.

Laser Focus.Name: Laser Focus
Laser Focus.Effects: The next succesful damaging attack made by the user is automatically a Critical Hit.

Last Resort.Name: Last Resort
Last Resort.Effects: Last Resort can only be used after the user has performed 5 other different Moves in its Move List during a single fight, without being switched out.

Leer.Name: Leer
Leer.Effects: All legal targets have their Defense lowered by -1 CS.

Lock-On.Name: Lock-On
Lock-On.Effects: The target is Locked-On. The next Move that the user uses against the Target that requires an Accuracy Check cannot miss. Lock-On's effect, on both the User and Target, can be passed by Baton Pass.

Lucky Chant.Name: Lucky Chant
Lucky Chant.Effects: Any user affected by Lucky Chant may activate it when receiving a Critical Hit to cause the attack to instead deal damage as if it was not a Critical Hit. Lucky Chant may be activated 3 times and then disappears.

Me First.Name: Me First
Me First.Effects: If an opponent declares a Damaging Attack against the user, and Me First’s user has a higher Speed stat then the target, the user may use Me First as an Interrupt. The User will then use the same Move the triggering foe was about to use on that foe.

Mean Look.Name: Mean Look
Mean Look.Effects: The Target becomes Trapped and Slowed for the remainder of the encounter.

Metronome.Name: Metronome
Metronome.Effects: Metronome randomly uses any other Move except for After You, Assist, Bestow, Copycat, Counter, Covet, Crafty Shield, Destiny Bond, Detect, Endure, Feint, Focus Punch, Follow Me, Helping Hand, King’s Shield, Metronome, Me First, Mimic, Mirror Coat, Mirror Move, Protect, Quash, Quick Guard, Rage Powder, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Snatch, Snore, Spiky Shield, Switcheroo, Thief, Transform, Trick, and Wide Guard. The GM helps to pick the random Move.

Milk Drink.Name: Milk Drink
Milk Drink.Effects: The target regains HP equal to half of its full HP. The user may target themselves with Milk Drink.

Mimic.Name: Mimic
Mimic.Effects: Choose a Move that the target has used during the encounter. For the remainder of the encounter, that Move replaces Mimic on the user’s Move List. Mimic cannot miss.

Mind Reader.Name: Mind Reader
Mind Reader.Effects: The target becomes Read to the user until the end of the user’s next turn. The user may end this effect when making an Attack on the user, causing that attack to automatically hit; OR when the Read target uses an Attack against the user, causing that attack to automatically miss. If the user has the Telepathy Capability, the user automatically succeeds on a mindreading attempt against the target, and may listen to the target’s surface thoughts as long as they remain Read. Mind Reader automatically misses against targets with the Mindlock Capability.

Minimize.Name: Minimize
Minimize.Effects: The user gains +4 Evasion, and the user's size is lowered to Small for the remainder of the encounter. *Grants Shrinkable

Morning Sun.Name: Morning Sun
Morning Sun.Effects: The user regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Point value. If it is Sunny, the user gains 2/3 of its full Hit Point value. If it is Rainy, Sand Storming or Hailing the user gains 1/4 of their full Hit Point value.

Multi-Attack.Name: Multi-Attack
Multi-Attack.Effects: Multi-Attack’s Type is determined by the Memory Disc, Plate, or Drive Item held.

Natural Gift.Name: Natural Gift
Natural Gift.Effects: Refer to the Move Keywords Berry list. Natural Gift deals damage according to the Berry list and Natural Gift’s Type is also defined there. The Berry’s Digestion/Food Buff is nullified and is not used.

Nature Power.Name: Nature Power
Nature Power.Effects: Nature Power uses a Move defined by the Environ keyword.

Noble Roar.Name: Noble Roar
Noble Roar.Effects: Noble Roar lowers all legal targets’ Attack and Special Attack by +1 CS.

Odor Sleuth.Name: Odor Sleuth
Odor Sleuth.Effects: Odor Sleuth may be activated as a Swift Action on the user’s turn. For the rest of the turn, the user’s Normal-Type and Fighting-Type Moves can hit and affect Ghost-Type targets, and the user can see through the Illusion Ability, Moves with the Illusion keyword, and effects created by the Illusionist Capability, ignoring all effects from those.

Pain Split.Name: Pain Split
Pain Split.Effects: The user and the target both lose 1/2 of their current Hit Points. Add the amount of Hit Points the user and the target lost together, and divide the value by 2. Both the target and the user gain Hit Points equal to this value. Do not add Injuries from Pain Split from Hit Point Markers until the full effect of the Move has been resolved. Pain Split never causes Massive Damage. Hit Point loss from Pain Split cannot be prevented in any way.

Pay Day.Name: Pay Day
Pay Day.Effects: Pay Day scatters metal coins equal in value to 1d8 times the user's level. If it is a trainer battle, the winner of the battle gets to pick up the coins.

Perish Song.Name: Perish Song
Perish Song.Effects: Perish Song cannot miss. All targets, including the user, receive a Perish Count of 3. At the beginning of each of the target’s turns, their Perish count is lowered by 1. Once a Perish Count reaches 0, set the Pokémon’s Hit Points to 0. A Perish Count disappears if a target returns to their Poké Ball, Takes a Breather, or is knocked out. Perish Song never causes Massive Damage.

Play Nice.Name: Play Nice
Play Nice.Effects: Play Nice lowers the target’s Attack by -1 CS.

Present.Name: Present
Present.Effects: Roll 1d6; Present has a DB equal to twice the result. On a result of 1, instead of taking damage the target gains 20 HP.

Protect.Name: Protect
Protect.Effects: If the user is hit by a Move, the user may use Protect. The user is instead not hit by the Move. The user does not take any damage nor is affected by any of the Move's effects.

Psych Up.Name: Psych Up
Psych Up.Effects: The user's Combat Stages are changed to match the target's Combat Stages. Psych Up cannot miss.

Rage.Name: Rage
Rage.Effects: The user becomes Enraged. Until the end of the user’s next turn, if the user is Enraged, the user gains +1 Attack Combat Stage whenever they are damaged by an Damaging Move or Attack.

Rapid Spin.Name: Rapid Spin
Rapid Spin.Effects: Rapid Spin destroys all Hazards within 5 meters, removes Leech Seeds, and removes the user's Trapped or Stuck status.

Razor Wind.Name: Razor Wind
Razor Wind.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user may not shift this round. The user whips up a whirlwind around themselves, granting +2 Evasion until the end of their next turn and destroying any Smokescreen or Hazards on any squares it is standing on and in all squares adjacent to it. Resolution Effect: The user attacks with Razor Wind. Razor Wind is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Recover.Name: Recover
Recover.Effects: The user regains HP equal to half of its full HP.

Recycle.Name: Recycle
Recycle.Effects: The effect of a consumable item used earlier in the encounter is used again as if it had not been destroyed. The item is still gone.

Reflect Type.Name: Reflect Type
Reflect Type.Effects: Reflect Type changes one of the user’s Types into one Type of your choice that the target has for the rest of the scene.

Refresh.Name: Refresh
Refresh.Effects: The user is cured of all Poison, Burns, and Paralysis.

Relic Song.Name: Relic Song
Relic Song.Effects: All legal targets fall Asleep on 16+. As long as Meloetta knows Relic Song, it may change between Aria Form and Step Form as a Swift Action when using Relic Song or as a Standard Action otherwise. Both Aria and Step Form must be statted with the same HP Stat.

Retaliate.Name: Retaliate
Retaliate.Effects: Retaliate's DB is doubled to DB 14 (4d10+15 / 40) if an ally has been Fainted by a Damaging Move used by the Target in the last 2 rounds of Combat.

Return.Name: Return
Return.Effects: Return's DB is equal to 3 plus the user's Loyalty Value.

Revelation Dance.Name: Revelation Dance
Revelation Dance.Effects: Revelation Dance is the same Type as the user’s primary Type (aka the first one in its Pokedex listing). Revelation Dance deals +5 Bonus Damage for every other Dance Move used by the user this round, to a maximum of +15.

Roar.Name: Roar
Roar.Effects: When declaring Roar, the user does nothing. At the end of the round, the user Shifts and uses Roar. Targets hit by Roar immediately Shift away from the user using their highest useable movement capability, towards their Trainer if possible. If the target is an owned Pokémon and ends this shift within 6 meters of their Poké Ball, they are immediately recalled to their Poké Ball. If that Trainer sends out a replacement, they do not lose their Command action.

Rock Climb.Name: Rock Climb
Rock Climb.Effects: Rock Climb Confuses the target on 17+.

Round.Name: Round
Round.Effects: Round's Damage Base is equal to 6, plus +2 more for each use of Round by any Trainer or Pokémon this round, up to a maximum of DB 12 (3d12+10 / 30).

Safeguard.Name: Safeguard
Safeguard.Effects: Blessing – Any user affected by Safeguard may activate it when receiving a Status Affliction to ignore the effects of that Status Affliction on their next turn. Safeguard may be activated 3 times, and then disappears.

Scary Face.Name: Scary Face
Scary Face.Effects: Lower the target’s Speed by -2 CS.

Screech.Name: Screech
Screech.Effects: Lower the Defense of all legal targets by -2 CS.

Secret Power.Name: Secret Power
Secret Power.Effects: Secret Power's effect depends on Environ. Secret Power's effect activates on 17+.

Self-Destruct.Name: Self-Destruct
Self-Destruct.Effects: The user's HP is set to -50% of its full HP. This HP loss may not be prevented or reduced in any way. The user's loyalty may be lowered.

Sharpen.Name: Sharpen
Sharpen.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack by +1 CS.

Shell Smash.Name: Shell Smash
Shell Smash.Effects: Raise the user's Attack, Special Attack, and Speed by +2 CS each. Lower the user's Defense and Special Defense by -1 CS each.

Simple Beam.Name: Simple Beam
Simple Beam.Effects: You choose one of the target's Abilities. Simple Beam changes that Ability to Simple for the remainder of the encounter.

Sing.Name: Sing
Sing.Effects: All legal Targets fall Asleep. On a miss, Sing instead causes targets to become Slowed and suffer a -2 penalty to their Evasion until the end of the user's next turn.

Sketch.Name: Sketch
Sketch.Effects: Sketch cannot miss. Once Sketch has been used, remove Sketch from the user's Move list. The last Move that the target used is added to the user's Move list permanently. Sketch may not be Interrupted or Intercepted.

Skull Bash.Name: Skull Bash
Skull Bash.Effects: Set-Up Effect: Raise the user's Defense by +1 CS. Resolution Effect: The user may attack with Skull Bash. The target is pushed 3 meters.

Slack Off.Name: Slack Off
Slack Off.Effects: The user regains HP equal to half of its full HP.

Slam.Name: Slam
Slam.Effects: Slam may be used as a Free Action at the end of a Sprint Maneuver taken as a Standard Action, as long as the user Shifted at least 3 meters in a straight line towards the target. When used this way, Slam gains the Smite keyword.

Slash.Name: Slash
Slash.Effects: Slash is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Sleep Talk.Name: Sleep Talk
Sleep Talk.Effects: Select another of the user’s Moves at random; this turn, the user may Shift and use that Move despite being Asleep. Sleep Talk can be only be used by Sleeping targets.

Smelling Salts.Name: Smelling Salts
Smelling Salts.Effects: If the target is Paralyzed, Smelling Salt’s Damage Base is doubled to 14 (4d10+15 / 40), and cures the target of Paralysis.

Smokescreen.Name: Smokescreen
Smokescreen.Effects: Smokescreen creates a blast of Smoke that covers the target area; the Smoke persists until the end of the encounter, or until Defog or Whirlwind are used. All targets attacking from or into the Smoke receive a -3 penalty to Accuracy.

Snore.Name: Snore
Snore.Effects: Snore Flinches all legal targets on 15+. Snore may only be used by Sleeping users.

Soft-Boiled.Name: Soft-Boiled
Soft-Boiled.Effects: The target regains Hit Points equal to half of its full Hit Points. The user may target themselves with Soft-Boiled.

Sonic Boom.Name: Sonic Boom
Sonic Boom.Effects: Sonicboom causes the target to lose 15 HP. Sonicboom is Special and interacts with other moves and effects as such (Special Evasion may be applied to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc.)

Spit Up.Name: Spit Up
Spit Up.Effects: For each Stockpiled Count the user has, Spit Up’s Damage Base is increased by +8. If the user has no Stockpiled count, Spit Up cannot be used.

Splash.Name: Splash
Splash.Effects: Shift Action - The user may make a single Jump, adding +1 to their Long Jump and High Jump values, and gains +2 Evasion until the end of their next turn. *Grants +1 Long Jump

Spotlight.Name: Spotlight
Spotlight.Effects: Until the end of the user’s next turn, the target is Blinded and Vulnerable.

Stockpile.Name: Stockpile
Stockpile.Effects: The user adds 1 to their Stockpiled count to a maximum of 3. For each number a Stockpiled count is above 0, raise the user’s Defense and Special Defense by +1 CS each. If a Stockpiled count is set to 0, any Combat Stages gained from the Stockpiled count are removed.

Stomp.Name: Stomp
Stomp.Effects: Stomp Flinches the target on 15+. If the target is at least one size category smaller than the user, Stomp deals an additional 10 damage.

Strength.Name: Strength
Strength.Effects: You may immediately initiate a Push Maneuver as a Free Action. The Maneuver automatically hits, but you must still make the Opposed Roll. *Grants +1 Power

Substitute.Name: Substitute
Substitute.Effects: The user loses 1/4 of their maximum Hit Points. This Hit Point loss cannot be prevented in any way. The user creates an Illusory Substitute Coat, which has Hit Points equal to 1/4th of the user’s full Hit Points +1. If the user would be hit by a Move or attack, instead the Substitute gets hit. Apply weakness, resistance and stats to the Substitute. The Substitute is immune to Status Afflictions and Status Moves. Moves with the Social or Sonic keywords completely ignore and bypass the Substitute. Once the Substitute has been destroyed, the user may be hit as normal. Substitute cannot be used if the user has less than 1/4 of their full Hit Points.

Super Fang.Name: Super Fang
Super Fang.Effects: The target loses 1/2 of its current HP.

Supersonic.Name: Supersonic
Supersonic.Effects: The target becomes Confused. On miss, the target suffers a -2 penalty to Accuracy Rolls for one full round.

Swagger.Name: Swagger
Swagger.Effects: Raise the target's Attack by +2 CS. The target is Confused.

Swallow.Name: Swallow
Swallow.Effects: If the user’s Stockpiled count is 1, they are healed 25% of their full Hit Point value; if their Stockpiled count is 2, they are healed half of their full Hit Point value; if their Stockpiled count is 3, they are healed back to full Hit Points. After using Swallow, the user’s Stockpiled count is set to 0. If the user has no Stockpiled count, Swallow does nothing.

Sweet Scent.Name: Sweet Scent
Sweet Scent.Effects: Targets hit by Sweet Scent gain a -2 Penalty to Evasion. (Total Evasion may not be lowered to a negative value.) *Grants Alluring

Swords Dance.Name: Swords Dance
Swords Dance.Effects: Raise the user's Attack by +2 CS.

Tail Whip.Name: Tail Whip
Tail Whip.Effects: All legal targets have their Defense lowered by -1 CS.

Take Down.Name: Take Down
Take Down.Effects: You may perform a Trip Maneuver against the target as a Free Action.

Tearful Look.Name: Tearful Look
Tearful Look.Effects: All legal targets lose -1 Attack and Special Attack CS each.

Techno Blast.Name: Techno Blast
Techno Blast.Effects: Techno Blast’s Type can be any Type while holding the appropriate Drive item or Plate item.

Thrash.Name: Thrash
Thrash.Effects: After damage is dealt, the user becomes Enraged and Confused.

Tickle.Name: Tickle
Tickle.Effects: Lower the target’s Attack and Defense by -1 CS each.

Transform.Name: Transform
Transform.Effects: The user targets a Pokémon within 10 meters and assumes the form of the target. It gains all of the target's Moves, Abilities, and Capabilities; and copies its weight and height. Transform lasts until the user is switched out, Fainted, or until the end of the encounter. The user may choose to end the Transformation on its turn as a free action, regaining its previous Move List. The user's Stats do not change from using Transform. Transform cannot miss.

Tri Attack.Name: Tri Attack
Tri Attack.Effects: Tri Attack gives the target a Status ailment on 17+. If this effect is triggered, roll 1d3; on 1 the target is Paralyzed; on 2 the target is Burned; on 3 the target is Frozen.

Trump Card.Name: Trump Card
Trump Card.Effects: Whenever the user uses Trump Card, the user gains a Trump Count after the attack is resolved. Trump Card's DB is increased by +2 for each Trump Count.

Uproar.Name: Uproar
Uproar.Effects: All Pokémon and Trainers within 5 meters of the user are cured of Sleep.

Weather Ball.Name: Weather Ball
Weather Ball.Effects: If it is Sunny, Weather Ball is Fire-Type. If it is Rainy, Weather Ball is Water-Type. If it is Hailing, Weather Ball is Ice-Type. If it is Sandstorming, Weather Ball is Rock-Type. When a weather effect is on the field, Weather Ball has a Damage Base of 10 (3d8+10 / 24). If there are multiple Weather Effects on the field, choose one type for Weather Ball to be that corresponds with an existing Weather Effect.

Whirlwind.Name: Whirlwind
Whirlwind.Effects: All targets are pushed X meters, where X is 8 minus their weight class. If the Line targets into a Smokescreen, the smoke is dispersed. All hazards in the Whirlwind are destroyed.

Wish.Name: Wish
Wish.Effects: At the end of the user's next turn, the target regains HP equal to half of its full HP. If the user targets itself and is replaced in battle, the replacement is healed by half of its own HP.

Work Up.Name: Work Up
Work Up.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack and Special Attack by +1 CS each.

Wrap.Name: Wrap
Wrap.Effects: The user gains a +1 Bonus to Accuracy Rolls made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers, and +2 to Skill Checks made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers or gain Dominance. Whenever the user gains Dominance in a Grapple, the target of the Grapple loses a Tick of Hit Points.

Wring Out.Name: Wring Out
Wring Out.Effects: For every 10% the target is below their full HP, Wring Out's Damage Base is reduced by -1.

Yawn.Name: Yawn
Yawn.Effects: The target falls Asleep at the end of its next turn. Yawn cannot miss.

Acid.Name: Acid
Acid.Effects: Acid lowers the target’s Defense by -1 Combat Stage on 18+.

Acid Armor.Name: Acid Armor
Acid Armor.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user becomes Liquefied. While Liquefied, the user is Slowed and cannot take Standard Actions except to Resolve the effect of Acid Armor, the user's Movement is never obstructed by rough or slow terrain, and the user can shift even through the smallest openings.
