Furthermore, while Liquefied, the user is completely immune to all Physical damage and becomes completely invisible if fully submerged in any liquid. Resolution Effect: The user gains +1 Defense CS, then stops being liquified.

Acid Spray.Name: Acid Spray
Acid Spray.Effects: Acid Spray lowers the target’s Special Defense by -2 CS.

Baneful Bunker.Name: Baneful Bunker
Baneful Bunker.Effects: If the user is hit by an attack, the user may use Baneful Bunker. The user is instead not hit by the Move. You do not take any damage nor are you affected by any of the Move’s effects. In addition, if the triggering attack was Melee ranged, the attacker is Poisoned.

Belch.Name: Belch
Belch.Effects: Belch cannot be used if the user has not traded in a Digestion/Food Buff during this Scene.

Clear Smog.Name: Clear Smog
Clear Smog.Effects: The target's Combat Stages are reset to their defaults, and all Coats on the target are destroyed. Clear Smog cannot miss.

Coil.Name: Coil
Coil.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack and Defense by +1 CS, and the user gains +1 Accuracy.

Cross Poison.Name: Cross Poison
Cross Poison.Effects: Cross Poison is a Critical Hit on 18+ and Poisons the target on 19+.

Gastro Acid.Name: Gastro Acid
Gastro Acid.Effects: The target's Ability is disabled until the end of the encounter. If the target has more than one ability, you choose one of them to disable.

Gunk Shot.Name: Gunk Shot
Gunk Shot.Effects: Gunk Shot Poisons the target on 15+.

Poison Fang.Name: Poison Fang
Poison Fang.Effects: Poison Fang Badly Poisons the target on 17+.

Poison Gas.Name: Poison Gas
Poison Gas.Effects: Poison Gas Poisons all legal targets.

Poison Jab.Name: Poison Jab
Poison Jab.Effects: Poison Jab Poisons the target on 15+.

Poison Sting.Name: Poison Sting
Poison Sting.Effects: Poison Sting Poisons the target on 17+.

Poison Tail.Name: Poison Tail
Poison Tail.Effects: Poison Tail is a Critical Hit on 18+ and Poisons the target on 19+.

Purify.Name: Purify
Purify.Effects: The target is cured of all Permanent and Volatile Statuses. For every status removed, the user recovers a Tick of Hit Points.

Sludge Bomb.Name: Sludge Bomb
Sludge Bomb.Effects: Sludge Bomb Poisons the target on 15+.

Sludge Wave.Name: Sludge Wave
Sludge Wave.Effects: Sludge Wave Poisons all legal targets on 19+.

Smog.Name: Smog
Smog.Effects: Smog Poisons all legal targets on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Toxic.Name: Toxic
Toxic.Effects: The target is Badly Poisoned. If the user is Poison Type, Toxic cannot miss.

Toxic Spikes.Name: Toxic Spikes
Toxic Spikes.Effects: Set 8 square meters of Toxic Spikes within the range such that all 8 meters are adjacent with at least one other space of Toxic Spikes. Toxic Spikes cause Terrain to become Slow Terrain, and a grounded foe that runs into the hazard becomes Poisoned and Slowed until the end of their next turn. If there are 2 layers of Toxic Spikes on the same space, it Badly Poisons the foes instead. Poison-Type Pokemon may move over Toxic Spikes harmlessly, destroying the Hazards as they do so.

Toxic Threads.Name: Toxic Threads
Toxic Threads.Effects: The target is Poisoned and receives -1 Speed Combat Stage. If the target is already Poisoned, they instead lose a Tick of Hit Points and receive -2 Speed Combat Stages.

Venom Drench.Name: Venom Drench
Venom Drench.Effects: All Poisoned targets have their Attack, Special Attack, and Speed lowered by -1 CS. Venom Drench cannot miss.

Venoshock.Name: Venoshock
Venoshock.Effects: If the target is Poisoned, Venoshock has a Damage Base of 13 (4d10+10 / 35) instead.

Agility.Name: Agility
Agility.Effects: Raise the user’s Speed 2 Combat Stages.

Ally Switch.Name: Ally Switch
Ally Switch.Effects: Ally Switch may be declared during a foe’s turn as an Interrupt. The user chooses one willing ally within 6 meters; the target and the user switch places. If the ally was a target of a Move, the user is now the target; If the user was a target of a Move, the ally is now the target.

Amnesia.Name: Amnesia
Amnesia.Effects: Raise the user’s Special Defense 2 Combat Stages.

Barrier.Name: Barrier
Barrier.Effects: The user creates a Barrier of psychic energy. The user places up to 4 segments of Barrier; each segment must be continuous with another segment, and at least one must be adjacent to the user. These barriers count as blocking terrain and last until the end of the encounter or until they are destroyed. Each Barrier segment is 2 meters tall, 1 meter wide, and 2 centimeters thick. Each segment has 20 Hit Points, 15 Damage Reduction, and takes damage as if it was Psychic Typed.

Calm Mind.Name: Calm Mind
Calm Mind.Effects: Raise the user’s Special Attack 1 Combat Stage and raise the user’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage.

Cosmic Power.Name: Cosmic Power
Cosmic Power.Effects: Raise the user’s Defense 1 Combat Stage and raise the user’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage.

Dream Eater.Name: Dream Eater
Dream Eater.Effects: Dream Eater can only target Sleeping Pokémon or Trainers. After the target takes damage, the user gains Hit Points equal to half of the damage they dealt to the target. Dream Eater does not wake up sleeping targets.

Future Sight.Name: Future Sight
Future Sight.Effects: Future Sight does nothing on the turn it is used. At the end of the user's next turn, Future Sight hits, even if the user is no longer on the field. Future Sight cannot miss.

Gravity.Name: Gravity
Gravity.Effects: For 5 rounds, the area is considered Warped. While Warped, Moves that involve the user being airborne may not be used. Pokémon cannot use Sky or Levitate Capabilities to end their turn at an altitude higher than 1 meter. Flying-Types and Pokémon with the Ability Levitate are no longer immune to Ground-Type Moves. All Accuracy Rolls receive a +2 Bonus.

Guard Split.Name: Guard Split
Guard Split.Effects: The target loses 5 Defense and 5 Special Defense. If they do, the user gains 5 Damage Reduction. These effects last until the end of the Scene.

Guard Swap.Name: Guard Swap
Guard Swap.Effects: The user and the target trade Combat Stage values for the Defense Stat, and then for the Special Defense Stat.

Heal Block.Name: Heal Block
Heal Block.Effects: Until the end of the encounter, the target may not gain HP or Temporary HP from any source. This effect ends if the target is switched out or Takes a Breather.

Healing Wish.Name: Healing Wish
Healing Wish.Effects: The user immediately Faints, lowering its HP to 0. The user takes no Injuries from HP Markers when using Healing Wish. The target is immediately cured of up to 3 injuries, healed to their Maximum Hit Points, and has the Frequency of all Moves restored. Healing Wish may target a Pokémon in a Poké Ball. Healing Wish does not restore the Frequency of Healing Wish or Lunar Dance. Injuries healed through Healing Wish count toward the total number of Injuries that can be healed each day, and this healing is limited by the same.

Heal Pulse.Name: Heal Pulse
Heal Pulse.Effects: Restores 50% of the target’s max Hit Points. Heal Pulse’s user may not target itself with Heal Pulse.

Heart Stamp.Name: Heart Stamp
Heart Stamp.Effects: Heart Stamp Flinches the target on 15+.

Heart Swap.Name: Heart Swap
Heart Swap.Effects: The targets trade Combat Stage values for each stat.

Imprison.Name: Imprison
Imprison.Effects: The target is Locked for the rest of the Scene. A Locked target may not use any Moves the user knows. Imprison cannot miss.

Instruct.Name: Instruct
Instruct.Effects: The target immediately reuses the attack it performed last, ignoring frequency, as a Free Action. They may choose new targets for the copied attack.

Kinesis.Name: Kinesis
Kinesis.Effects: If the user or an Ally within 6 meters is about to be hit by an attack, the user may use Kinesis as an interrupt. The triggering Accuracy Roll receives a -4 penalty. This may cause Moves to miss.

Light Screen.Name: Light Screen
Light Screen.Effects: Blessing – Any user affected by Light Screen may activate it when receiving Special Damage to resist the Damage one step. Light Screen may be activated 2 times, and then disappears.

Lunar Dance.Name: Lunar Dance
Lunar Dance.Effects: The user immediately Faints, lowering its Hit Points to 0. The user takes no Injuries from Hit Point Markers when using Lunar Dance. The target is immediately cured of up to 3 injuries, healed to their Maximum Hit Points, and has the Frequency of all Moves restored. Lunar Dance may target a Pokémon in a Poké Ball. Lunar Dance does not restore the Frequency of Healing Wish or Lunar Dance. Injuries healed through Lunar Dance count toward the total number of Injuries that can be healed each day, and this healing is limited by the same.

Luster Purge.Name: Luster Purge
Luster Purge.Effects: Luster Purge lowers the target's Special Defense by -1 CS on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Magic Coat.Name: Magic Coat
Magic Coat.Effects: If the user is about to get a hit by a Move that does not have a Damage Dice Roll, they may use Magic Coat as an Interrupt. The Interrupted Move’s user is treated as if they were the target of their own Move, with the user of Magic Coat as the user.

Magic Room.Name: Magic Room
Magic Room.Effects: The area becomes Useless for 5 rounds. While Useless, Pokémon may not benefit from the effects of any Held Items, and Trainers cannot benefit from any Accessory-Slot equipment. This does not affect consumable or activated items, only Items with Static effects or Triggers.

Meditate.Name: Meditate
Meditate.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack 1 Combat Stage.

Miracle Eye.Name: Miracle Eye
Miracle Eye.Effects: Miracle Eye may be activated as a Swift Action on the user’s turn. For the rest of the turn, the user’s Psychic-Type Moves can hit and affect Dark-Type targets, and the user can see through the Illusion Ability, Moves with the Illusion keyword, and effects created by the Illusionist Capability, ignoring all effects from those.

Mirror Coat.Name: Mirror Coat
Mirror Coat.Effects: Mirror Coat may be used as a Reaction when the user is hit by a damaging Special Attack. Resolve the Triggering Attack, with Mirror Coat’s user resisting the attack one step further. After the attack is resolved, if Mirror Coat’s user was not Fainted, the triggering foe then loses Hit Points equal to twice the amount of Hit Points lost by the user from the triggering attack. Note that Mirror Coat is Special, and while it cannot miss, it cannot hit targets immune to Psychic-Type Moves.

Mist Ball.Name: Mist Ball
Mist Ball.Effects: Mist Ball lowers the target’s Special Attack by 1 Combat Stage on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Power Split.Name: Power Split
Power Split.Effects: The target has their Attack and Special Attack lowered by 5. If they do, the user gains a +5 bonus to Damage Rolls. These effects last until the end of the scene.

Power Swap.Name: Power Swap
Power Swap.Effects: The user and the target trade Combat Stage values for the Attack Stat, and then for the Special Attack Stat.

Power Trick.Name: Power Trick
Power Trick.Effects: The user's Attack stat and Defense stat are switched for the remainder of the encounter, or until the user is switched out or Fainted.

Psychic.Name: Psychic
Psychic.Effects: The target is Pushed 1 meter in any direction. Psychic lowers the target’s Special Defense 1 Combat Stage on 17+.  Grants Telekinetic.

Psychic Fangs.Name: Psychic Fangs
Psychic Fangs.Effects: Light Screen and Reflect cannot be declared in response to Psychic Fangs.

Psychic Terrain.Name: Psychic Terrain
Psychic Terrain.Effects: The Field becomes Weird for five rounds. While the Field is Weird, non-Flying and non- Levitating Pokemon cannot declare Priority or Interrupt Moves outside their own Initiatives. Damaging Psychic-Type attacks deal an additional 10 damage.

Psycho Boost.Name: Psycho Boost
Psycho Boost.Effects: Lower the user's Special Attack by -2 Combat Stages after damage is resolved.

Psycho Cut.Name: Psycho Cut
Psycho Cut.Effects: Psycho Cut is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Psycho Shift.Name: Psycho Shift
Psycho Shift.Effects: The user is cured of a Status ailment and the target is given that Status ailment. Psycho Shift cannot miss. Psycho Shift can only be used if the user has a Status ailment and the target does not have the status ailment that is being transferred.

Psyshock.Name: Psyshock
Psyshock.Effects: When calculating damage, the target subtracts their Defense from Psyshock's damage instead of their Special Defense. Psyshock is still otherwise Special (Special Evasion is used to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc.)

Psystrike.Name: Psystrike
Psystrike.Effects: When calculating damage, the target subtracts their Defense from Psystrike's damage instead of their Special Defense. Psystrike is still otherwise Special (Special Evasion is used to avoid it, Mirror Coat can reflect it, etc.)

Psywave.Name: Psywave
Psywave.Effects: Roll 1d4; on 1 the target loses HP equal to half the user's Level; on 2 the target loses HP equal to the user's Level; on 3 the target loses HP equal to 1.5x the user's level; on 4 the target loses HP equal to the user's Level doubled. Do not apply weakness or resistance, and do not apply Stats. Do apply Immunity.

Reflect.Name: Reflect
Reflect.Effects: Blessing – Any user affected by Reflect may activate it when receiving Physical Damage to resist the Damage one step. Reflect may be activated 2 times, and then disappears.

Rest.Name: Rest
Rest.Effects: The user is set to their full Hit Point value. The user is cured of any Status ailments. Then, the user falls Asleep. The user cannot make Sleep Checks at the beginning of their turn. They are cured of the Sleep at the end of their turn in 2 rounds.

Role Play.Name: Role Play
Role Play.Effects: The user gains one of the target's Abilities, chosen at random, for the remainder of the encounter. This effect ends if the user Faints or is switched out. Role Play cannot miss.

Skill Swap.Name: Skill Swap
Skill Swap.Effects: The user loses one of their Abilities, selected by the user, and gains one the target’s Abilities, selected at random, for the remainder of encounter. The target loses the copied Ability, and gains the user’s lost Ability. This effect ends if either the target or the user is Switched out or Fainted, but only for that Pokémon or Trainer.

Speed Swap.Name: Speed Swap
Speed Swap.Effects: The user and the target trade Initiative values.

Stored Power.Name: Stored Power
Stored Power.Effects: For every Combat Stage the user has above 0, add +2 to Stored Power’s Damage Base, up to a maximum of Damage Base 20.

Synchronoise.Name: Synchronoise
Synchronoise.Effects: Synchronoise can only hit targets that share a type with Synchronoise's user.

Telekinesis.Name: Telekinesis
Telekinesis.Effects: The target becomes Lifted. While Lifted, they gain the Levitate Ability, are Slowed, and lose all Movement Capabilities except for the Levitate 4 granted by Levitate (reduced to 2 by the Slow condition). While Lifted, the user may not apply any Evasion bonuses to determine whether they are hit by Moves or not. The Lifted target may use a Shift Action to roll 1d20; on a result of 16+, they stop being Lifted. *Grants Telekinetic

Teleport.Name: Teleport
Teleport.Effects: The user Teleports up to X meters, where X is its Teleporter Capability. Any Move that targeted Teleport's user continue through the desired target's space if the Move allows for it as if the user hadn't been there; single target moves simply miss. *Grants Teleporter 4

Trick.Name: Trick
Trick.Effects: Both targets must be hit for Trick to succeed. The user may target itself or willing allies with Trick; you do not need to roll for Accuracy Check in these cases. Both targets lose their Held Item and gain the other target's Held Item. If a target has no Held Item, they still can gain the other target's Held Item.

Trick Room.Name: Trick Room
Trick Room.Effects: Starting at the beginning of the next round, for 5 rounds, the area is considered Rewinding. While Rewinding, Initiative is reversed, and participants instead go from lowest Initiative to highest.

Wonder Room.Name: Wonder Room
Wonder Room.Effects: For 5 rounds, the area is considered Wondered. While Wondered, each individual Pokémon's Defense and Special Defense are switched.

Zen Headbutt.Name: Zen Headbutt
Zen Headbutt.Effects: Zen Headbutt Flinches the target on 15+.

Ancient Power.Name: Ancient Power
Ancient Power.Effects: The user has each of its stats raised by +1 CS on 19+.

Diamond Storm.Name: Diamond Storm
Diamond Storm.Effects: Diamond Storm raises the User’s Defense by +1 CS on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Rock Polish.Name: Rock Polish
Rock Polish.Effects: Raise the user's Speed by +2 CS.

Rock Slide.Name: Rock Slide
Rock Slide.Effects: Rock Slide Flinches all legal targets on 17+.

Rock Tomb.Name: Rock Tomb
Rock Tomb.Effects: Rock Tomb lowers the target's Speed by -1 CS. *Grants Materializer

Rollout.Name: Rollout
Rollout.Effects: The user continues to use Rollout on each of its turns until they miss any target with Rollout, or are not able to hit any target with Rollout during their turn. Each successive use of Rollout increases Rollout’s Damage Base by +4 to a maximum of DB 15.

Sandstorm.Name: Sandstorm
Sandstorm.Effects: The weather changes to a Sandstorm for 5 rounds. While it is Sandstorming, all non-Ground, Rock, or Steel Type Pokémon lose a Tick of Hit Points at the beginning of their turn.

Smack Down.Name: Smack Down
Smack Down.Effects: The target is knocked down to ground level, and loses all Sky or Levitate Speeds for 3 turns. During this time, they may be hit by Ground-Type Moves even if normally immune.

Stealth Rock.Name: Stealth Rock
Stealth Rock.Effects: Set 4 square meters of Stealth Rock hazards within 6 meters. If a foe moves within 2 meters of a space occupied by Rocks, move at most one Rock to the offender, then destroy the Rock. When that happens, the Stealth Rock causes a foe to lose a Tick of Hit Points. Stealth Rock is considered to be dealing damage; Apply Weakness and Resistance. Do not apply stats. A Pokémon who has been hit by a Stealth Rock Hazard cannot get hit by another in the same encounter until it is returned to a Poké Ball and then sent back out. *Grants Materializer

Stone Edge.Name: Stone Edge
Stone Edge.Effects: Stone Edge is a Critical Hit on 17+.

Wide Guard.Name: Wide Guard
Wide Guard.Effects: If an Ally adjacent to Wide Guard’s user is hit by a Move, you may use Wide Guard as an Interrupt. All targets adjacent to Wide Guard’s user, including the user, are instead not hit by the triggering Move and do not suffer any of its effects.

Anchor Shot.Name: Anchor Shot
Anchor Shot.Effects: The Target is Trapped for 2 rounds. Anchor Shot may only be used from the user's Anchor Token.

Autotomize.Name: Autotomize
Autotomize.Effects: For the remainder of the Encounter, the user’s Weight Class is one value lower, to a minimum of 1. If the user can, the user’s Speed is raised by +2 Combat Stages.

Doom Desire.Name: Doom Desire
Doom Desire.Effects: Doom Desire does nothing on the turn it is used. At the end of the user's next turn, Doom Desire hits, even if the user if no longer on the field. Doom Desire cannot miss.

Flash Cannon.Name: Flash Cannon
Flash Cannon.Effects: Flash Cannon lowers the target's Special Defense by -1 CS on 17+.

Gear Up.Name: Gear Up
Gear Up.Effects: All targets with the Plus or Minus Abilities receive +1 Attack and Special Attack CS each.

Gyro Ball.Name: Gyro Ball
Gyro Ball.Effects: The target reveals their Speed Stat (including Combat Stages). If it is higher than the user’s (including Combat Stages), subtract the user’s Speed Stat from the target’s and apply the difference as Bonus Damage.

Heavy Slam.Name: Heavy Slam
Heavy Slam.Effects: For each weight class the user is above the target, increase Heavy Slam's Damage Base by +2.

Iron Defense.Name: Iron Defense
Iron Defense.Effects: Raise the user's Defense by +2 CS.

Iron Head.Name: Iron Head
Iron Head.Effects: Iron Head Flinches the target on 15+.

Iron Tail.Name: Iron Tail
Iron Tail.Effects: Iron Tail lowers the target’s Defense by -1 CS on 19+.

King's Shield.Name: King's Shield
King's Shield.Effects: If the user is hit by an attack, the user may use King’s Shield. The user is instead not hit by the Move. You do not take any damage nor are you affected by any of the Move’s effects. In addition, if the triggering attack was Melee ranged, the attacker’s Attack is lowered by -2 CS.

Metal Burst.Name: Metal Burst
Metal Burst.Effects: Metal Burst causes all legal targets in the burst to lose HP equal to the total amount of direct Damage the user has taken since the beginning of this Round. Metal Burst cannot miss.

Metal Claw.Name: Metal Claw
Metal Claw.Effects: Raise the user's Attack by +1 CS on 18+.

Metal Sound.Name: Metal Sound
Metal Sound.Effects: All Legal Targets have their Special Defense lowered by -2 CS.

Meteor Mash.Name: Meteor Mash
Meteor Mash.Effects: Raise the user's Attack by +1 CS on 15+.

Mirror Shot.Name: Mirror Shot
Mirror Shot.Effects: All Legal Targets have their Accuracy lowered by -2 on 16+.

Shift Gear.Name: Shift Gear
Shift Gear.Effects: Raise the user’s Attack by +1 CS and Speed by +2 CS.

Steel Wing.Name: Steel Wing
Steel Wing.Effects: Steel Wing raises the user's Defense by +1 CS on 15+.

Sunsteel Strike.Name: Sunsteel Strike
Sunsteel Strike.Effects: This Move ignores any Abilities that would cause it to fail or miss; those Abilities cannot be activated in response to Sunsteel Strike (ex: Dodge, Wonder Guard)

Aqua Ring.Name: Aqua Ring
Aqua Ring.Effects: Aqua Ring covers the user in a Coat that heals the user at the beginning of their turn. The user is healed a Tick of Hit Points each turn.

Brine.Name: Brine
Brine.Effects: If the target’s Hit Points are under 50%, Brine’s Damage Base is increased to Damage Base 13 (4d10+10 / 35).

Bubble.Name: Bubble
Bubble.Effects: Bubble lowers the target's Speed by -1 CS on 16+..

Bubblebeam.Name: Bubblebeam
Bubblebeam.Effects: Bubblebeam lowers the target's Speed by -1 CS on 18+.

Clamp.Name: Clamp
Clamp.Effects: The user gains a +1 Bonus to Accuracy Rolls made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers, and +2 to Skill Checks made to initiate Grapple Maneuvers or gain Dominance. Whenever the user gains Dominance in a Grapple, the target of the Grapple loses a Tick of Hit Points.

Crabhammer.Name: Crabhammer
Crabhammer.Effects: Crabhammer is a Critical Hit on 18+.

Dive.Name: Dive
Dive.Effects: Set-Up Effect: The user moves underwater and its turn ends. The user must be in water at least 10 meters deep to use Dive. While underwater, the user may not be targeted by Moves. Resolution Effect: The user may shift horizontally using their underwater speed, and then may shift straight up until reaching a target. The user then attacks with Dive, creating a Burst 1. *Grants Swim +3

Hydro Pump.Name: Hydro Pump
Hydro Pump.Effects: The target is pushed away from the user 3 meters.

Liquidation.Name: Liquidation
Liquidation.Effects: The target's Defense is lowered by -1 CS on 17+.

Muddy Water.Name: Muddy Water
Muddy Water.Effects: As a Shift Action, the user may Move to any open square in Muddy Water’s area of effect without provoking any Attacks of Opportunity. On 16+, the Accuracy of all targets is lowered by 1.

Octazooka.Name: Octazooka
Octazooka.Effects: Octazooka lowers the target's Accuracy by -1 on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Rain Dance.Name: Rain Dance
Rain Dance.Effects: The weather becomes Rainy for 5 rounds. While Rainy, Water-Type Attacks gain a +5 bonus to Damage Rolls, and Fire-Type Attacks suffer a -5 Damage penalty.

Razor Shell.Name: Razor Shell
Razor Shell.Effects: Razor Shell lowers the target's Defense by -1 CS on an Even-Numbered Roll.

Soak.Name: Soak
Soak.Effects: The target gains the Water type in addition to its other Types for 5 turns.

Sparkling Aria.Name: Sparkling Aria
Sparkling Aria.Effects: When you hit a target with Sparkling Aria, the user may choose to deal no damage and instead cures that target of Burn, Confusion, Infatuation, Rage, or Provocation.

Surf.Name: Surf
Surf.Effects: As a Shift Action, the user may Move to any open square in Surf ’s area of effect without provoking any Attacks of Opportunity.

Water Pledge.Name: Water Pledge
Water Pledge.Effects: If an ally uses Fire Pledge or Grass Pledge, you may use Water Pledge as Priority (Advanced) immediately after their turn to target the same foe. If used in conjunction with Fire Pledge, a Rainbow is created that lasts for 5 rounds. If used in conjunction with Grass Pledge, the target and all foes adjacent to the target are slowed and have their Speed reduced by 2 Combat Stages. Consult the Pledge keyword for additional details.

Water Pulse.Name: Water Pulse
Water Pulse.Effects: Water Pulse Confuses the target on 17+.

Water Sport.Name: Water Sport
Water Sport.Effects: All targets in the burst, including the user, gain a Coat which grants them 1 Step of Resistance to Fire Type Moves. After a target has been hit by a damaging Fire Type Move, the coat is removed. *Grants Fountain

Water Spout.Name: Water Spout
Water Spout.Effects: For each 10% of HP the user is missing, Water Spout's Damage Base is reduced by -1. Water Spout creates a 1 meter burst, but also affects an area 10 meters tall straight up.

Whirlpool.Name: Whirlpool
Whirlpool.Effects: The target is put in a Vortex.

Withdraw.Name: Withdraw
Withdraw.Effects:
The user becomes Withdrawn. While Withdrawn, the user becomes immune to Critical Hits and gain 15 Damage Reduction. However, while Withdrawn, the user cannot Shift, and may only use self-targeting Moves. The user may stop being Withdrawn as a Shift Action.
September Playtest: The user’s Defense is raised 1 Combat Stage.

Arcane Fury.Name: Arcane Fury
Arcane Fury.Effects: Arcane Fury’s Targets become Vulnerable on 19+.

Energy Sphere.Name: Energy Sphere
Energy Sphere.Effects: You gain +1 Special Defense Combat Stage on 19+.

Rending Spell.Name: Rending Spell
Rending Spell.Effects: The target loses a Tick of Hit Points on 16+.

Resonance Beam.Name: Resonance Beam
Resonance Beam.Effects: All targets have their Special Defense lowered by 1 Combat Stage on 20+. This Effect Range is extended by +1 for each foe targeted by this Move.

Secret Force.Name: Secret Force
Secret Force.Effects:
When calculating damage, the target subtracts their Defense from Secret Force’s damage instead of their Special Defense. Secret Force is still otherwise Special.
Limitation: Melee Weapons Only

Arcane Storm.Name: Arcane Storm
Arcane Storm.Effects:
All targets of Arcane Storm are Slowed and Vulnerable for 1 Full Round.
Limitation: Ranged Weapons only

Bane.Name: Bane
Bane.Effects: The target loses a Tick of Hit Points at the start of their next three turns and suffers a -2 penalty to all Save Checks on those turns.

Cone of Force.Name: Cone of Force
Cone of Force.Effects:
Cone of Force Pushes all targets 2 meters, and lowers their Evasion by -2 for 1 full round..
Limitation: Melee Weapons Only

Energy Vortex.Name: Energy Vortex
Energy Vortex.Effects: The target is put in a Vortex.

Magic Burst.Name: Magic Burst
Magic Burst.Effects:
Foes hit by Magic Burst can’t make Attacks of Opportunity for 1 full round.
Limitation: Melee Weapons Only

Spirit Lance.Name: Spirit Lance
Spirit Lance.Effects: Spirit Lance deals +3 damage to all targets for each target beyond the first that it successfully hits.

Bash!.Name: Bash!
Bash!.Effects: Bash! lowers the target’s Initiative to 0 for 1 full round on 15+.

Bullseye.Name: Bullseye
Bullseye.Effects:
Bullseye is a Critical Hit on 16+.
Limitation: Ranged Weapons Only

Cheap Shot.Name: Cheap Shot
Cheap Shot.Effects:
Cheap Shot cannot miss.
Limitation: Small Melee and Short Ranged Weapons Only

Double Swipe.Name: Double Swipe
Double Swipe.Range: WR, 2 Targets; or WR, 1 Target, Double Strike

Pierce!.Name: Pierce!
Pierce!.Effects: Pierce deals an additional +10 damage against targets with Damage Reduction.

Take Aim.Name: Take Aim
Take Aim.Effects: Raise the user’s Accuracy by +1. If the user performs an Weapon Move on their next turn that deals damage, add its Damage Dice Roll an extra time to the damage.

Wear Down.Name: Wear Down
Wear Down.Effects: Wear Down lowers the target’s Defense by 1 Combat Stage on Even-Numbered Rolls.

Wounding Strike.Name: Wounding Strike
Wounding Strike.Effects: The target loses a Tick of Hit Points.

Bleed!.Name: Bleed!
Bleed!.Effects: The target loses a Tick of Hit Points at the start of their next three turns.

Deadly Strike.Name: Deadly Strike
Deadly Strike.Effects:
If Deadly Strike Hits, it is a Critical Hit.
Limitation: Not usable by Large Melee Weapons.

Furious Strikes.Name: Furious Strikes
Furious Strikes.Effects:
For each hit rolled on your Five Strike roll, the target of the attack has their Evasion reduced by 1 for one full round.
Limitation: Melee or Short Ranged Weapons Only

Gouge.Name: Gouge
Gouge.Effects:
If both hits of Gouge successfully hit the target, the target gains an Injury.
Limitation: Small Melee and Short Ranged Weapons Only

Maul.Name: Maul
Maul.Effects:
The target is Flinched.
Limitation: Melee Weapons Only

Riposte.Name: Riposte
Riposte.Effects:
Trigger: Your Target misses you with a melee Attack.
Limitations: Melee or Short-Ranged Weapons Only

Sweeping Strike.Name: Sweeping Strike
Sweeping Strike.Effects:
You may attempt a Trip Maneuver against the target as a free action.
Limitation: Short-Range Weapons or Weapons with the Reach Quality Only

Titanic Slam.Name: Titanic Slam
Titanic Slam.Effects:
On Even-Numbered Rolls, the target is Slowed for one full round.
Limitation: Melee Weapons Only

Triple Threat.Name: Triple Threat
Triple Threat.Effects: Limitation: Large Melee Weapons and Long-Range Weapons Only

Attack of Opportunity.Name: Attack of Opportunity
Attack of Opportunity.Effects:
You may make a Struggle Attack against the triggering foe as an Interrupt. You may use Attack of Opportunity only once per round. Attacks of Opportunity cannot be made by Sleeping, Flinched, or Paralyzed targets. Attacks of Opportunity can be triggered in multiple ways:
»» An adjacent foe uses a Push, Grapple, Disarm, Trip, or Dirty Trick Maneuver that does not target you.
»» An adjacent foe stands up.
»» An adjacent foe uses a Ranged Attack that does not target someone adjacent to it.
»» An adjacent foe uses a Standard Action to pick up or retrieve an item.
»» An adjacent foe Shifts out of a Square adjacent to you.

Disengage.Name: Disengage
Disengage.Effects: You may Shift 1 Meter. Shifting this way does not provoke an Attack of Opportunity.

Disarm.Name: Disarm
Disarm.Effects: You and the target each make opposed Combat or Stealth Checks. If you win, the target’s Held Item (Main Hand or Off-Hand for humans) falls to the ground.

Dirty Trick.Name: Dirty Trick
Dirty Trick.Effects: You may perform any of the following Dirty Tricks: Hinder, Blind, or Low Blow. You may use each trick only once each Scene per target. Input each Dirty Trick for details.

Hinder.Name: Hinder
Hinder.Effects: You and the target make Opposed Athletics Checks. If you win, the target is Slowed and takes a -2 penalty to all Skill Checks for one full round.

Blind.Name: Blind
Blind.Effects: You and the target make Opposed Stealth Checks. If you win, the target is Blinded for one full round.

Low Blow.Name: Low Blow
Low Blow.Effects: You and the target make Opposed Acrobatics Checks. If you win, the target is Vulnerable and has their Initiative set to 0 until the end of your next turn.

Grapple.Name: Grapple
Grapple.Effects:
You and the target each make opposed Combat or Athletics Checks. If you win, you and the target each become Grappled, and you gain Dominance in the Grapple.

Pokémon and Trainers that are Grappled
»» Are Vulnerable
»» Cannot take Shift Actions, or any actions that would cause them to Shift.
»» Gain a -6 penalty to Accuracy Rolls if targeting anyone outside of the Grapple.
»» Additionally, Grapple has other effects on whether the target has or doesn’t have Dominance.

If a target begins their turn as a part of a Grapple but with no Dominance, they may choose to contest the Grapple as a Full Action. If they do, all participants make opposed Combat or Athletics Check. Whoever wins then may choose to either continue the Grapple and gain Dominance, or to end the Grapple.

If a target has the Phasing or Teleporter Capability, they may also use those to escape from a Grapple on their turn with no check required.

If a target begins their turn as part of a Grapple and has Dominance, they may take one of the following actions as a Full Action.
»» End the Grapple.
»» Secure: They gain a +3 Bonus to the next opposed check they make in the Grapple.
»» Attack: They may automatically hit with an Unarmed Struggle Attack.
»» Move: They Shift, dragging the other person in the grapple with them. The user’s Movement Capability is lowered by the other grappler’s Weight Class.

Intercept Melee.Name: Intercept Melee
Intercept Melee.Effects:
Trigger: An ally within Movement range is hit by an adjacent foe.
Effect: You must make an Acrobatics or Athletics Check, with a DC equal to three times the number of meters they have to move to reach the triggering Ally; If you succeed, you Push the triggering Ally 1 Meter away from you, and Shift to occupy their space, and are hit by the triggering attack. On Failure to make the Check, the user still Shifts a number of meters equal a third of their check result.

Note: If the target that was Intercepted was hit by an Area of Effect Move, and the 1 meter push does not remove them from the Area of Effect, the Intercept has no effect since they are still in the area of the attack – it would cause the Interceptor to be hit by the Move however.

Special: Pokemon must have a Loyalty of 3 or greater to make Intercept Melee and Intercept range Maneuvers and may only Intercept attacks against their Trainer. At Loyalty 6, Pokemon may Intercept for any Ally.

Additional Rules
»» Pokémon and Trainers may only Intercept against Priority and Interrupt Moves if they are faster than the user of those Moves.
»» Moves that cannot miss (such as Aura Sphere or Swift) cannot be Intercepted.
»» Pokémon and Trainers cannot attempt Intercepts if they are Asleep, Confused, Enraged, Frozen, Stuck, Paralyzed, or otherwise unable to move.
»» Intercepts may not be used to move the Intercepting Pokémon or Trainer OUT of the way of an attack. They will always be hit, regardless.

Intercept Ranged.Name: Intercept Ranged
Intercept Ranged.Effects:
Trigger: A Ranged X-Target attack passes within your Movement Range.
Effect: Select a Square within your Movement Range that lies directly between the source of the attack and the target of the attack. Make an Acrobatics or Athletics Check; you may Shift a number of Meters equal to half the result towards the chosen square. If you succeed, you take the attack instead of its intended target. If you fail, you still Shift a number of Meters equal to half the result.

Special: Pokemon must have a Loyalty of 3 or greater to make Intercept Melee and Intercept range Maneuvers and may only Intercept attacks against their Trainer. At Loyalty 6, Pokemon may Intercept for any Ally.

Additional Rules
»» Pokémon and Trainers may only Intercept against Priority and Interrupt Moves if they are faster than the user of those Moves.
»» Moves that cannot miss (such as Aura Sphere or Swift) cannot be Intercepted.
»» Pokémon and Trainers cannot attempt Intercepts if they are Asleep, Confused, Enraged, Frozen, Stuck, Paralyzed, or otherwise unable to move.
»» Intercepts may not be used to move the Intercepting Pokémon or Trainer OUT of the way of an attack. They will always be hit, regardless.

Manipulate.Name: Manipulate
Manipulate.Effects: You may perform any of the following Manipulations: Bon Mot, Flirt, or Terrorize. You may use each Manipulation only once each Scene per target. Manipulate can only be performed by Trainers. Input each Manipulation for details.

Bon Mot.Name: Bon Mot
Bon Mot.Effects: Make a Guile Check, opposed by the target’s Guile or Focus. If you win, the target is Enraged and cannot spend AP for one full round. The target does not gain a Save Check against this effect.

Flirt.Name: Flirt
Flirt.Effects: Make a Charm Check, opposed by the target’s Charm or Focus. If you win, the target is Infatuated with you for one full round. The target automatically fails their Save Check.

Terrorize.Name: Terrorize
Terrorize.Effects: Make an Intimidate Check, opposed by the target’s Intimidate or Focus. If you win, the target loses all Temporary Hit Points and can only use At-Will Frequency Moves for one full round.

Push.Name: Push
Push.Effects: You and the target each make opposed Combat or Athletics Checks. If you win, the target is Pushed back 1 Meter directly away from you. If you have Movement remaining this round, you may then Move into the newly occupied Space, and Push the target again. This continues until you choose to stop, or have no Movement remaining for the round. Push may only be used against a target whose weight is no heavier than your Heavy Lifting rating.

Sprint.Name: Sprint
Sprint.Effects: Increase your Movement Speeds by 50% for the rest of your turn.

Trip.Name: Trip
Trip.Effects: You and the target each make opposed Combat or Acrobatics Checks. If you win, the target is knocked over and Tripped.

Abominable.Name: Abominable

Abominable.Effect 2: The user ignores the Recoil Keyword when attacking, and does not gain injuries from Massive Damage.

Ambush.Effect 2: The user may use a Melee Move with a Damage Base of 6 (before applying STAB or other modifiers) or lower as if it had the Priority keyword. If it hits, the target is Flinched.

Analytic.Effect 2: Whenever the user targets uses a damaging Move on a Pokémon or Trainer that have acted before it during Initiative this Round, that Move deals an additional +5 Damage.

Anger Point.Effect 2: When the Pokémon receives a Critical Hit, they become Enraged and gain +6 Attack Combat Stages.

Anticipation.Name: Anticipation

Anticipation.Effect 2:

Anticipation only reveals whether the opponent does or does not have those moves, not the specific moves themselves.

Aqua Boost.Name: Aqua Boost

The user may end the effect as a Free Action, and the effect ends if the user is fainted or returned to a Poké Ball.
Arena Trap.Effect 2:
Target - Pokémon or Trainers

The user may end the effect as a Free Action, and the effect ends if the user is fainted or returned to a Poké Ball.

Aroma Veil.Effect 2: The user and all Pokémon and Trainers within 3 meters cannot be Confused, Enraged, or Suppressed. Defensive.

Aura Break.Effect 2: Foes may not benefit from Abilities that increase the Combat Stages or damage dealt by themselvs or their allies.

Bad Dreams.Effect 2: At the beginning of the user’s turn, all Sleeping Pokémon or Trainers in a Burst 5 lose a Tick of Hit Points.

Battle Armor.Effect 2: The user is immune to Critical Hits; they are instead normal hits. Defensive.

Color Theory.Name: Color Theory

Upon gaining this ability at Birth, the user rolls 1d12 to determine the color of their tail secretions. 1 = Red; 2 = Red-Orange; 3 = Orange; 4 = Yellow- Orange; 5 = Yellow; 6 = Yellow-Green; 7 = Green; 8 = Blue-Green; 9 = Blue; 10 = Blue-Violet; 11 = Violet; 12 = Red-Violet.

Red is tied to Attack, Orange is tied to Defense, Yellow is tied to Special Attack, Green is tied to Special Defense, Blue is tied to Speed, Violet is tied to HP. Users with a “Pure” Color (Red, Orange, Yellow, etc) gain a +6 Bonus to the Base Stat tied to their color. Users with a “Mixed” Color (Red-Orange, Yellow-Orange, etc) gain a +3 Bonus to each Stat tied to the color.

Upon gaining this ability at Birth, the user rolls 1d12 to determine the color of their tail secretions. 1 = Red; 2 = Red-Orange; 3 = Orange; 4 = Yellow- Orange; 5 = Yellow; 6 = Yellow-Green; 7 = Green; 8 = Blue-Green; 9 = Blue; 10 = Blue-Violet; 11 = Violet; 12 = Red-Violet.

Poison Point.Trigger: The user is hit by a Melee Move
Poison Point.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user is hit by a Melee Move
The attacking foe is Poisoned.

Poison Touch.Name: Poison Touch
Poison Touch.Effect: The Pokémon’s Moves which deal damage Poison Legal Targets on 19+. If a move already has a chance of Poisoning foes, Poison Touch increases the effect range by +2.
Poison Touch.Effect 2: The Pokémon’s Moves which deal damage Poison Legal Targets on 19+. If a move already has a chance of Poisoning foes, Poison Touch increases the effect range by +2.

Poltergeist.Name: Poltergeist
Poltergeist.Effect:
Rotom gains an Ability and a Move depending on what Form it has taken. This Move cannot be forgotten or replaced in any way.

Standard Rotom: Move - Thunder Shock. Ability - Levitate.
Heat Rotom: Move- Overheat. Ability - Levitate.
Wash Rotom: Move - Hydro Pump. Ability - Aqua Boost.
Frost Rotom: Move - Blizzard. Ability - Frostbite.
Fan Rotom: Move - Air Slash. Ability - Keen Eye
Mow Rotom: Move - Leaf Storm. Ability - Grass Pelt.
Poltergeist.Effect 2:
Rotom gains an Ability and a Move depending on what Form it has taken. This Move cannot be forgotten or replaced in any way.

Standard Rotom: Move - Thunder Shock. Ability - Levitate.
Heat Rotom: Move- Overheat. Ability - Levitate.
Wash Rotom: Move - Hydro Pump. Ability - Aqua Boost.
Frost Rotom: Move - Blizzard. Ability - Frostbite.
Fan Rotom: Move - Air Slash. Ability - Keen Eye
Mow Rotom: Move - Leaf Storm. Ability - Grass Pelt.

Polycephaly.Name: Polycephaly
Polycephaly.Effect: The user may make Struggle Attacks as a Swift Action. Struggle Attacks made this way are resisted one step further than they normally would be.
Polycephaly.Effect 2: The user may make Struggle Attacks as a Swift Action. Struggle Attacks made this way are resisted one step further than they normally would be.

Prankster.Name: Prankster
Prankster.Effect: The user may use Status Moves as Priority (Advanced).
Prankster.Effect 2: The user may use Status Moves as Priority (Advanced).

Pressure.Name: Pressure
Pressure.Effect: While within 3 meters of the user, all foes are Suppressed. This effect ends when the user is Fainted.
Pressure.Effect 2: While within 3 meters of the user, all foes are Suppressed. This effect ends when the user is Fainted.

Pride.Name: Pride
Pride.Effect: While suffering from Burn, Poison, Paralysis, Freezing, or while Asleep, the user’s Special Attack is raised 2 Combat Stages. If suffering from none of these conditions, the user loses any Combat Stages gained this way.
Pride.Effect 2: While suffering from Burn, Poison, Paralysis, Freezing, or while Asleep, the user’s Special Attack is raised 2 Combat Stages. If suffering from none of these conditions, the user loses any Combat Stages gained this way.

Prime Fury.Name: Prime Fury
Prime Fury.Effect: The user becomes Enraged, and gains +1 Attack Combat Stage.
Prime Fury.Effect 2: The user becomes Enraged, and gains +1 Attack Combat Stage.

Probability Control.Name: Probability Control
Probability Control.Effect: The user may reroll any roll, or have any ally reroll any roll that has been made. This leaves discoverable Psychic residue.
Probability Control.Target: Any roll made by yourself or an ally.
Probability Control.Effect 2:
Target - Any roll made by yourself or an ally.
The user may reroll any roll, or have any ally reroll any roll that has been made. This leaves discoverable Psychic residue.

Protean.Name: Protean
Protean.Effect: The user’s Type changes to match the Type of the triggering Move. This Ability resolves before the Move is resolved (And thus you may apply STAB, and trigger other Features and Abilities appropriately).
Protean.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user uses a Move.
The user’s Type changes to match the Type of the triggering Move. This Ability resolves before the Move is resolved (And thus you may apply STAB, and trigger other Features and Abilities appropriately).

Pumpkingrab.Name: Pumpkingrab
Pumpkingrab.Effect: The user gains a +4 bonus to Accuracy Checks of Struggle Attacks made to initiate Grapple, and a +3 Bonus to Skill Checks made to initiate a Grapple.
Pumpkingrab.Effect 2: The user gains a +4 bonus to Accuracy Checks of Struggle Attacks made to initiate Grapple, and a +3 Bonus to Skill Checks made to initiate a Grapple.

Pure Blooded.Name: Pure Blooded
Pure Blooded.Effect: The user gains Last Chance with Dragon.
Pure Blooded.Effect 2:
Keywords - Last Chance
The user gains Last Chance with Dragon.

Pure Power.Name: Pure Power
Pure Power.Effect: The Pokémon's base attack stat is doubled. This may double any bonuses from Nature or Vitamins, but not bonuses from Features.
Pure Power.Effect 2: The Pokémon's base attack stat is doubled. This may double any bonuses from Nature or Vitamins, but not bonuses from Features.

Quick Cloak.Name: Quick Cloak
Quick Cloak.Effect: Burmy quickly builds a cloak out of nearby materials; using leaves and twigs will give it a Grass Plant Cloak, using sand and rocks will give it a Ground Sandy Cloak, and using trash or scrap will give it a Steel Trash Cloak. While in a Cloak, Burmy gains the Type associated with the Cloak as a secondary Typing, which will become permanent upon evolution into Wormadam. Cloaks are destroyed if Burmy is hit for Super-Effective Damage, or if Burmy makes a new Cloak.
Quick Cloak.Effect 2: Burmy quickly builds a cloak out of nearby materials; using leaves and twigs will give it a Grass Plant Cloak, using sand and rocks will give it a Ground Sandy Cloak, and using trash or scrap will give it a Steel Trash Cloak. While in a Cloak, Burmy gains the Type associated with the Cloak as a secondary Typing, which will become permanent upon evolution into Wormadam. Cloaks are destroyed if Burmy is hit for Super-Effective Damage, or if Burmy makes a new Cloak.

Quick Curl.Name: Quick Curl
Quick Curl.Effect: Connection - Defense Curl. The user may activate this Ability to use Defense Curl as a Swift Action.
Quick Curl.Effect 2: Connection - Defense Curl. The user may activate this Ability to use Defense Curl as a Swift Action.

Quick Feet.Name: Quick Feet
Quick Feet.Effect: When Poisoned, Burned, Paralyzed, Frozen or put to Sleep, the user’s Speed is raised 2 Combat Stages. The user does not lose Speed Combat Stages from Paralysis. If the user is healed all Status Conditions, their Speed is lowered appropriately.
Quick Feet.Effect 2: When Poisoned, Burned, Paralyzed, Frozen or put to Sleep, the user’s Speed is raised 2 Combat Stages. The user does not lose Speed Combat Stages from Paralysis. If the user is healed all Status Conditions, their Speed is lowered appropriately.

Rain Dish.Name: Rain Dish
Rain Dish.Effect: While Rainy, the user gains a Tick of Hit Points at the beginning of each of their turns.
Rain Dish.Effect 2: While Rainy, the user gains a Tick of Hit Points at the beginning of each of their turns.

Rally.Name: Rally
Rally.Effect: All allies within 10 meters may immediately shift 1 Meter in any direction they wish. Rally does not work on sleeping, flinched, stuck, fainted, or otherwise incapacitated allies. Rally does not work on the user.
Rally.Effect 2: All allies within 10 meters may immediately shift 1 Meter in any direction they wish. Rally does not work on sleeping, flinched, stuck, fainted, or otherwise incapacitated allies. Rally does not work on the user.

Rattled.Name: Rattled
Rattled.Effect: The user's Speed is raised by +1 Combat Stage.
Rattled.Trigger: The user is hit by a Bug, Dark, or Ghost Type Move
Rattled.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user is hit by a Bug, Dark, or Ghost Type Move
The user's Speed is raised by +1 Combat Stage.

Razor Edge.Name: Razor Edge
Razor Edge.Effect: Connection - Poison Tail. The user's Critical Hit Range on all Moves is increased by +2; any Moves with "Tail" in their name have their Critical Hit Range increased by +3 instead.
Razor Edge.Effect 2: Connection - Poison Tail. The user's Critical Hit Range on all Moves is increased by +2; any Moves with "Tail" in their name have their Critical Hit Range increased by +3 instead.

Reckless.Name: Reckless
Reckless.Effect: Increase the Damage Base of the moves Jump Kick, Hi Jump Kick, and moves with the Recoil Keyword by +2.
Reckless.Effect 2: Increase the Damage Base of the moves Jump Kick, Hi Jump Kick, and moves with the Recoil Keyword by +2.

Refreshing Veil.Name: Refreshing Veil
Refreshing Veil.Effect: Connection – Aqua Ring. Whenever the user activates Aqua Ring, they may activate this Feature to cure themselves of all Persistent Status Effects.
Refreshing Veil.Effect 2: Connection – Aqua Ring. Whenever the user activates Aqua Ring, they may activate this Feature to cure themselves of all Persistent Status Effects.

Refridgerate.Name: Refridgerate
Refridgerate.Effect: The Move is changed to be Ice Type.
Refridgerate.Trigger: The user uses a Normal Type Damaging Move.
Refridgerate.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user uses a Normal Type Damaging Move.
The Move is changed to be Ice Type.

Regal Challenge.Name: Regal Challenge
Regal Challenge.Effect: Make an AC4 Status Attack against the target. If the attack hits, lower the target’s Speed by 1 Combat Stage and the target is Slowed. If the attack misses, raise the user’s Attack and Special Attack by +1 Combat Stage each.
Regal Challenge.Effect 2:
Target - Pokémon or Trainer within 5 Meters
Make an AC4 Status Attack against the target. If the attack hits, lower the target’s Speed by 1 Combat Stage and the target is Slowed. If the attack misses, raise the user’s Attack and Special Attack by +1 Combat Stage each.

Regenerator.Name: Regenerator
Regenerator.Effect: The user gains Hit Points equal to 1/3rd of its maximum Hit Points. Regenerator may be activated only once per Scene.
Regenerator.Trigger: The user is recalled into a Pokeball or Takes a Breather.
Regenerator.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user is recalled into a Pokeball or Takes a Breather.
The user gains Hit Points equal to 1/3rd of its maximum Hit Points. Regenerator may be activated only once per Scene.

Rivalry.Name: Rivalry
Rivalry.Effect: Whenever the user deals direct damage to a target of the same gender, increase the Damage dealt by +5.
Rivalry.Effect 2: Whenever the user deals direct damage to a target of the same gender, increase the Damage dealt by +5.

Rock Head.Name: Rock Head
Rock Head.Effect: The user ignores the Recoil keyword when attacking.
Rock Head.Effect 2: The user ignores the Recoil keyword when attacking.

Rocket.Name: Rocket
Rocket.Effect: The user’s Sky capability is increased by +3 until the end of the user’s next turn, and the user goes first on the following round, ignoring initiative; Interrupt Moves may not be used in response to their Moves that round.
Rocket.Effect 2: The user’s Sky capability is increased by +3 until the end of the user’s next turn, and the user goes first on the following round, ignoring initiative; Interrupt Moves may not be used in response to their Moves that round.

Root Down.Name: Root Down
Root Down.Effect: Connection - Ingrain. While the user has the Ingrain Coat, they may activate this Ability to gain Temporary Hit Points equal to 1/16th of their Max Hit Points.
Root Down.Effect 2: Connection - Ingrain. While the user has the Ingrain Coat, they may activate this Ability to gain Temporary Hit Points equal to 1/16th of their Max Hit Points.

Rough Skin.Name: Rough Skin
Rough Skin.Effect: The attacker loses a tick of Hit Points.
Rough Skin.Trigger: The user is hit by a damaging Melee Attack
Rough Skin.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user is hit by a damaging Melee Attack
The attacker loses a tick of Hit Points.

Run Away.Name: Run Away
Run Away.Effect: The user cannot be Slowed, Stuck, or Trapped. The user does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity by Shifting.
Run Away.Effect 2: The user cannot be Slowed, Stuck, or Trapped. The user does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity by Shifting.

Run Up.Name: Run Up
Run Up.Effect: If the user moves in a straight line to a target and uses a damaging Melee Attack, it may add the number of meters traveled in a direct line as Bonus Damage to a Damage Roll.
Run Up.Effect 2: If the user moves in a straight line to a target and uses a damaging Melee Attack, it may add the number of meters traveled in a direct line as Bonus Damage to a Damage Roll.

Sand Force.Name: Sand Force
Sand Force.Effect: While in a Sandstorm, the user's Ground, Rock, and Steel-Type Direct-Damage Moves deal +5 Damage. Additionally, the user is immune to damage from Sandstorms.
Sand Force.Effect 2: While in a Sandstorm, the user's Ground, Rock, and Steel-Type Direct-Damage Moves deal +5 Damage. Additionally, the user is immune to damage from Sandstorms.

Sand Rush.Name: Sand Rush
Sand Rush.Effect: While the Weather is a Sandstorm, the user gains +4 Speed Combat Stages. Additionally, the user is immune to damage from Sandstorms.
Sand Rush.Effect 2: While the Weather is a Sandstorm, the user gains +4 Speed Combat Stages. Additionally, the user is immune to damage from Sandstorms.

Sand Stream.Name: Sand Stream
Sand Stream.Effect: The Weather changes to a Sandstorm for 5 rounds. As a static effect, the user is not damaged by Sandstorm.
Sand Stream.Effect 2: The Weather changes to a Sandstorm for 5 rounds. As a static effect, the user is not damaged by Sandstorm.

Sand Veil.Name: Sand Veil
Sand Veil.Effect: The user’s Evasion is increased by +2 while in a Sandstorm. The user and allies adjacent to the user are not damaged by the Sandstorm.
Sand Veil.Effect 2: The user’s Evasion is increased by +2 while in a Sandstorm. The user and allies adjacent to the user are not damaged by the Sandstorm.

Sap Sipper.Name: Sap Sipper
Sap Sipper.Effect: The user is immune to the damage and effects of Grass Type attacks. If a damaging Grass Type attack hits the user, the user gains +1 Attack Combat Stage. Defensive.
Sap Sipper.Effect 2: The user is immune to the damage and effects of Grass Type attacks. If a damaging Grass Type attack hits the user, the user gains +1 Attack Combat Stage. Defensive.

Scrappy.Name: Scrappy
Scrappy.Effect: Ghosts are not immune to the user's Normal and Fighting-Type Moves.
Scrappy.Effect 2: Ghosts are not immune to the user's Normal and Fighting-Type Moves.

Sequence.Name: Sequence
Sequence.Effect: For every allied Electric-Type Pokémon cardinally adjacent to the user, raise the user’s Attack and Special Attack by +1 CS each before calculating damage for the triggering attack. After the attack is resolved, lose all Combat Stages gained this way.
Sequence.Trigger: The user uses an Electric Attack
Sequence.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user uses an Electric Attack
For every allied Electric-Type Pokémon cardinally adjacent to the user, raise the user’s Attack and Special Attack by +1 CS each before calculating damage for the triggering attack. After the attack is resolved, lose all Combat Stages gained this way.

Serene Grace.Name: Serene Grace
Serene Grace.Effect: The users Effect Range is increased by +2.
Serene Grace.Effect 2: The users Effect Range is increased by +2.

Serpent's Mark.Name: Serpent's Mark
Serpent's Mark.Effect:
Arbok’s Advanced and High Abilities depend on the Arbok’s hood pattern. To determine its pattern, roll 1d6 upon evolution or upon generation. If an Arbok is bred, it will have the same pattern as its parent. If both parents are Arboks with different patterns, determine the pattern randomly.

Pattern Name - Adv Ability / High Ability
1) Attack Pattern - Rivalry / Strong Jaw
2) Crush Pattern - Unnerve / Crush Trap
3) Fear Pattern - Frighten / Regal Challenge
4) Life Pattern – Regenerator / Defy Death
5) Speed Pattern - Run Away / Speed Boost
6) Stealth Pattern - Instinct / Infiltrator
Serpent's Mark.Effect 2:
Arbok’s Advanced and High Abilities depend on the Arbok’s hood pattern. To determine its pattern, roll 1d6 upon evolution or upon generation. If an Arbok is bred, it will have the same pattern as its parent. If both parents are Arboks with different patterns, determine the pattern randomly.

Pattern Name - Adv Ability / High Ability
1) Attack Pattern - Rivalry / Strong Jaw
2) Crush Pattern - Unnerve / Crush Trap
3) Fear Pattern - Frighten / Regal Challenge
4) Life Pattern – Regenerator / Defy Death
5) Speed Pattern - Run Away / Speed Boost
6) Stealth Pattern - Instinct / Infiltrator

Shackle.Name: Shackle
Shackle.Effect: Shackle creates a Burst 3. All foes in the burst have their movement capabilities halved until the end of their next turn.
Shackle.Effect 2: Shackle creates a Burst 3. All foes in the burst have their movement capabilities halved until the end of their next turn.

Shadow Tag.Name: Shadow Tag
Shadow Tag.Effect: The target’s shadow becomes pinned to the target’s current spot for 5 turns. During this time, the target is Slowed and Trapped, and cannot move more than 5 meters from the spot their shadow is pinned to; even being Pushed and other forced movement effects cannot force the target to Move more than 5 meters from that spot.
Shadow Tag.Effect 2:
Target - An adjacent Trainer or Pokémon
The target’s shadow becomes pinned to the target’s current spot for 5 turns. During this time, the target is Slowed and Trapped, and cannot move more than 5 meters from the spot their shadow is pinned to; even being Pushed and other forced movement effects cannot force the target to Move more than 5 meters from that spot.

Shed Skin.Name: Shed Skin
Shed Skin.Effect: The user is cured of one of Paralysis, Freezing, Burns, Poison, or Sleep.
Shed Skin.Effect 2: The user is cured of one of Paralysis, Freezing, Burns, Poison, or Sleep.

Sheer Force.Name: Sheer Force
Sheer Force.Effect: If a Pokémon with Sheer Force uses a Move with a secondary effect that triggers during Accuracy Roll, increase that Move's Base Damage by +2. However, the secondary effects of Move never trigger. This does not affect Critical Hits, or moves with increased Critical Hit ranges.
Sheer Force.Effect 2: If a Pokémon with Sheer Force uses a Move with a secondary effect that triggers during Accuracy Roll, increase that Move's Base Damage by +2. However, the secondary effects of Move never trigger. This does not affect Critical Hits, or moves with increased Critical Hit ranges.

Shell Armor.Name: Shell Armor
Shell Armor.Effect: The user is immune to Critical Hits; they are instead normal hits. Defensive.
Shell Armor.Effect 2: The user is immune to Critical Hits; they are instead normal hits. Defensive.

Shell Cannon.Name: Shell Cannon
Shell Cannon.Effect: When Blastoise uses Aqua Jet, Dive, Flash Cannon, Hydro Cannon, Hydro Pump, Tackle, Waterfall, Water Gun, and Water Spout they may activate this Ability to gain +2 to their Accuracy Roll and deals +4 Bonus Damage with Damage Rolls. When using Aqua Jet, Dive, Tackle, or Waterfall, Blastoise must shift in a straight line to their target to activate this Ability, but their Overland and Swim Speeds are increased by +2 when doing so.
Shell Cannon.Effect 2: When Blastoise uses Aqua Jet, Dive, Flash Cannon, Hydro Cannon, Hydro Pump, Tackle, Waterfall, Water Gun, and Water Spout they may activate this Ability to gain +2 to their Accuracy Roll and deals +4 Bonus Damage with Damage Rolls. When using Aqua Jet, Dive, Tackle, or Waterfall, Blastoise must shift in a straight line to their target to activate this Ability, but their Overland and Swim Speeds are increased by +2 when doing so.

Shell Shield.Name: Shell Shield
Shell Shield.Effect: Connection - Withdraw. The user may activate this Ability to use Withdraw as an Interrupt and a Free Action. The user must still use a Shift Action to stop being Withdrawn.
Shell Shield.Effect 2: Connection - Withdraw. The user may activate this Ability to use Withdraw as an Interrupt and a Free Action. The user must still use a Shift Action to stop being Withdrawn.

Shield Dust.Name: Shield Dust
Shield Dust.Effect: The user ignores the secondary effects that trigger during Accuracy Roll of damaging Moves that target the user. For example, Flamethrower can never inflict the Burn Condition. Defensive.
Shield Dust.Effect 2: The user ignores the secondary effects that trigger during Accuracy Roll of damaging Moves that target the user. For example, Flamethrower can never inflict the Burn Condition. Defensive.

Silk Threads.Name: Silk Threads
Silk Threads.Effect: Connection - String Shot. Whenever the user uses "String Shot", the target becomes Slowed until the end of their next turn.
Silk Threads.Effect 2: Connection - String Shot. Whenever the user uses "String Shot", the target becomes Slowed until the end of their next turn.

Simple.Name: Simple
Simple.Effect: When the Pokémon’s Combat Stages are altered, double the amount of Combat Stages they are raised or lowered.
Simple.Effect 2: When the Pokémon’s Combat Stages are altered, double the amount of Combat Stages they are raised or lowered.

Skill Link.Name: Skill Link
Skill Link.Effect: The Triggering Move automatically hits 5 Times.
Skill Link.Trigger: The user hits with a Move with the Five Strike keyword.
Skill Link.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user hits with a Move with the Five Strike keyword.
The Triggering Move automatically hits 5 Times.

Slow Start.Name: Slow Start
Slow Start.Effect: For 3 rounds after joining an encounter, the Pokémon’s Speed and Attack Stats are halved and they have 10 Damage Reduction.
Slow Start.Effect 2: For 3 rounds after joining an encounter, the Pokémon’s Speed and Attack Stats are halved and they have 10 Damage Reduction.

Sniper.Name: Sniper
Sniper.Effect: When the Pokémon gets a Critical Hit, add the value of the Damage Dice Roll an additional time to the total damage.
Sniper.Effect 2: When the Pokémon gets a Critical Hit, add the value of the Damage Dice Roll an additional time to the total damage.

Snow Cloak.Name: Snow Cloak
Snow Cloak.Effect: The user's Evasion is increased by +2 while in Hail. The user and allies adjacent to the user are not damaged by Hail.
Snow Cloak.Effect 2: The user's Evasion is increased by +2 while in Hail. The user and allies adjacent to the user are not damaged by Hail.

Snow Warning.Name: Snow Warning
Snow Warning.Effect: The Weather changes to Hail for 5 rounds. As a static effect the user is not damaged by Hail.
Snow Warning.Effect 2: The Weather changes to Hail for 5 rounds. As a static effect the user is not damaged by Hail.

Solar Power.Name: Solar Power
Solar Power.Effect: When Sunny, the Pokémon loses 1/16th of its Max HP at the beginning of its turn. When Sunny, its Special Attack Stat is increased by 2 Combat Stages.
Solar Power.Effect 2: When Sunny, the Pokémon loses 1/16th of its Max HP at the beginning of its turn. When Sunny, its Special Attack Stat is increased by 2 Combat Stages.

Solid Rock.Name: Solid Rock
Solid Rock.Effect: When the user is hit by a Super-Effective attack, the attack deals 1.25x damage instead of x1.5 damage. If the user is hit by a Super-Super-Effective attack, the attack deals x1.5 damage instead of x2 damage. If you have both Solid Rock and Filter, you gain 5 Damage eduction against Super-Effective Damage. Defensive.
Solid Rock.Effect 2: When the user is hit by a Super-Effective attack, the attack deals 1.25x damage instead of x1.5 damage. If the user is hit by a Super-Super-Effective attack, the attack deals x1.5 damage instead of x2 damage. If you have both Solid Rock and Filter, you gain 5 Damage eduction against Super-Effective Damage. Defensive.

Sonic Courtship.Name: Sonic Courtship
Sonic Courtship.Effect: Connection - Attract. Treat Attract as a Cone 2 Move with the Sonic keyword for this use, which effects all targets regardless of Gender.
Sonic Courtship.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user uses Attract
Connection - Attract. Treat Attract as a Cone 2 Move with the Sonic keyword for this use, which effects all targets regardless of Gender.

Soothing Tone.Name: Soothing Tone
Soothing Tone.Effect: Connection - Heal Bell. Whenever the user uses the Move Heal Bell, all targets that recovered from a Status ailment gain a Tick of Hit Points.
Soothing Tone.Effect 2: Connection - Heal Bell. Whenever the user uses the Move Heal Bell, all targets that recovered from a Status ailment gain a Tick of Hit Points.

Soulstealer.Name: Soulstealer
Soulstealer.Effect: The user removes one Injury from themselves and recovers 25% of their Maximum Hit Points. If the triggering attack killed its target, the user instead removes all Injuries and recovers all Hit Points.
Soulstealer.Trigger: The user’s attack causes a foe to Faint
Soulstealer.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user’s attack causes a foe to Faint
The user removes one Injury from themselves and recovers 25% of their Maximum Hit Points. If the triggering attack killed its target, the user instead removes all Injuries and recovers all Hit Points.

Sound Lance.Name: Sound Lance
Sound Lance.Effect: Connection – Supersonic. The target of Supersonic takes Special Normal-Type damage equal to the user’s Special Attack score. This effect functions independently of whether Supersonic hits its target.
Sound Lance.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user uses Supersonic
Connection – Supersonic. The target of Supersonic takes Special Normal-Type damage equal to the user’s Special Attack score. This effect functions independently of whether Supersonic hits its target.

Soundproof.Name: Soundproof
Soundproof.Effect: The Pokémon is immune to Moves with the Sonic Keyword. Defensive.
Soundproof.Effect 2: The Pokémon is immune to Moves with the Sonic Keyword. Defensive.

Speed Boost.Name: Speed Boost
Speed Boost.Effect: The Pokémon’s Speed is raised 1 Combat Stage at the end of each of its turns. Speed Boost has no effect while out of combat.
Speed Boost.Effect 2: The Pokémon’s Speed is raised 1 Combat Stage at the end of each of its turns. Speed Boost has no effect while out of combat.

Spinning Dance.Name: Spinning Dance
Spinning Dance.Effect: If not Fainted, Paralyzed, or Asleep, the user gains +1 Evasion and may immediately Shift 1 meter.
Spinning Dance.Trigger: The user is targeted by an attack, but is missed
Spinning Dance.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user is targeted by an attack, but is missed
If not Fainted, Paralyzed, or Asleep, the user gains +1 Evasion and may immediately Shift 1 meter.

Spiteful Intervention.Name: Spiteful Intervention
Spiteful Intervention.Effect: Connection -  Spite.  The user may use Spite in response to an attack hitting an ally, in addition to hitting themselves.
Spiteful Intervention.Effect 2: Connection -  Spite.  The user may use Spite in response to an attack hitting an ally, in addition to hitting themselves.

Spray Down.Name: Spray Down
Spray Down.Effect: The triggering attack’s target is knocked down to ground level, and loses all Sky or Levitate Speeds for 3 turns. During this time, they may be hit by Ground-Type Moves even if normally immune.
Spray Down.Trigger: The user hits an airborne target with a ranged 1-target attack.
Spray Down.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user hits an airborne target with a ranged 1-target attack.
The triggering attack’s target is knocked down to ground level, and loses all Sky or Levitate Speeds for 3 turns. During this time, they may be hit by Ground-Type Moves even if normally immune.

Sprint.Name: Sprint
Sprint.Effect: The user gains +2 Speed Combat Stages. Additionally, the user's Overland Speed is always increased by +2.
Sprint.Trigger: The user uses the Sprint Action during Combat
Sprint.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user uses the Sprint Action during Combat
The user gains +2 Speed Combat Stages. Additionally, the user's Overland Speed is always increased by +2.

Static.Name: Static
Static.Trigger: The user is hit by a Melee Attack
Static.Effect 2:
Trigger - The user is hit by a Melee Attack
The attacking foe becomes Paralyzed.

Stall.Name: Stall
Stall.Effect: In a round’s queue, a Pokémon with Stall is always last. If a Pokémon goes to the end of the queue, the Pokémon with Stall is still the last to move. The user’s actions taken on their Initiative Count (not Priority or Interrupt) cannot be Interrupted.
Stall.Effect 2: In a round’s queue, a Pokémon with Stall is always last. If a Pokémon goes to the end of the queue, the Pokémon with Stall is still the last to move. The user’s actions taken on their Initiative Count (not Priority or Interrupt) cannot be Interrupted.

Stance Change.Name: Stance Change
Stance Change.Effect: Aegislash has two Stances: Shield Stance and Sword Stance. Its default Stance is Shield Stance. Whenever Aegislash uses a damaging attack, it switches to Sword Stance and swaps its Attack Stat with its Defense and its Special Attack Stat with its Special Defense, without changing Combat Stages. Whenever Aegislash uses King’s Shield, Protect, a Status Move that raises Defense Combat Stages, or a Blessing, it switches to Shield Stance and swaps its offensive and defensive Stats back to their original arrangement. Aegislash may also change its Stance as a Full Action.
Stance Change.Effect 2: Aegislash has two Stances: Shield Stance and Sword Stance. Its default Stance is Shield Stance. Whenever Aegislash uses a damaging attack, it switches to Sword Stance and swaps its Attack Stat with its Defense and its Special Attack Stat with its Special Defense, without changing Combat Stages. Whenever Aegislash uses King’s Shield, Protect, a Status Move that raises Defense Combat Stages, or a Blessing, it switches to Shield Stance and swaps its offensive and defensive Stats back to their original arrangement. Aegislash may also change its Stance as a Full Action.

Starlight.Name: Starlight
Starlight.Effect: The user may activate Starlight while exposed to moonlight or starlight to become Luminous. While the user is Luminous, all foes suffer a -2 penalty to Accuracy Rolls against the user. The user may expend the Luminous condition upon hitting a foe with a damaging attack to cause that foe to become Confused.
Starlight.Effect 2: The user may activate Starlight while exposed to moonlight or starlight to become Luminous. While the user is Luminous, all foes suffer a -2 penalty to Accuracy Rolls against the user.
